RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/De.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Deranged Archaeologist Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/De.description: The '''Deranged archaeologist Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Deranged archaeologist]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Runite bar.name: Runite bar
Runite bar.description: For [[free-to-play]], apart from smelting, [[Bryophyta]] is the only way of obtaining runite bars.

Ardougne teleport (tablet).name: Ardougne teleport (tablet)
Ardougne teleport (tablet).description: Players with level 51 [[Magic]] can create this item on a [[Teak eagle lectern]] or better in a [[player-owned house]]. This requires 2 [[law rune]]s, 2 [[water rune]]s, and 1 [[soft clay]]. Creating a tablet grants 61 Magic experience, the same as casting the Ardougne Teleport spell. [[Elemental staves]] can be substituted for [[runes]] and are recommended when making teleport tablets in large groups at a time.

Amulet of nature.name: Amulet of nature
Amulet of nature.description: {{Mes|A low hum resonates from the Amulet of Nature - it seeks audience with you.}}

Twisted Banshee.name: Twisted Banshee
Twisted Banshee.description: As they are undead, the [[Crumble Undead]] spell and the [[Salve amulet]] '''do''' work on them.

Ice plateau teleport (tablet).name: Ice plateau teleport (tablet)
Ice plateau teleport (tablet).description: Because this tablet teleports players to the Wilderness, a warning will appear upon clicking the "Break" option on the tablet. This can be toggled by right-clicking the "Configure" option.

Dragonstone bolts (e).name: Dragonstone bolts (e)
Dragonstone bolts (e).description: If the target is immune to dragonfire, the special effect will not activate. This also applies to players using [[Protect from Magic]], which likewise fully blocks the dragonstone bolts from activating.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/Lone_Identity/status/1297787741640331264|date=24 August 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/M3vkF|archivedate=23 December 2022|quote=[Does Protect From Magic offer any protection against enchanted Dragonstone bolts, or any of the Dragonfire/Wyvern shields' special attacks?] The blurite jade and runite dragonstone bolts' special effects are blocked by that prayer, so it would do the normal attacks against a player who's using that prayer. (...)}}

Magus icon.name: Magus icon
Magus icon.description: The icon must be brought to a [[furnace]], alongside three [[chromium ingot]]s and a [[ring mould]], to craft the [[magus ring]]. The entire process requires level 90 [[Magic]] and 80 [[Crafting]], which can be boosted.

Pay-to-play Prayer training.name: Pay-to-play Prayer training
Pay-to-play Prayer training.description: Other important milestones include Level 50 for completing all quests, Level 77 for unlocking all prayers and Level 85 for completing all [[Achievement Diaries]].

Exchange:Raging echoes relic hunter (t3).name: Exchange:Raging echoes relic hunter (t3) armour set

Steel heraldic helm (Zamorak).name: Steel heraldic helm (Zamorak)
Steel heraldic helm (Zamorak).description: Players need level {{SCP|prayer|70|link=yes}} in order to create the helm. Players can use a [[Heraldry space|painting stand]] in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Strange Machine.name: Strange Machine
Strange Machine.description: The southernmost machine in the House on the Hill can be used to upgrade the [[digsite pendant]]. By using the pendant on the Strange Machine, players will unlock a teleport to the House on the Hill, which allows them to easily access the [[Mycelium Transportation System]] on the island.

Mahogany pyre logs.name: Mahogany pyre logs
Mahogany pyre logs.description: Once the sacred oil has been obtained players will need to use '''three doses''' of it upon some [[mahogany logs]]. These logs will then become '''Mahogany pyre logs''' and the player is granted 14 Firemaking experience.

Flamtaer bracelet.name: Flamtaer bracelet
Flamtaer bracelet.description: When equipped, each build at the [[Shades of Mort'ton (minigame)|Shades of Mort'ton]] temple will become substantially more effective. The bracelet will provide 80 charges before disappearing. With a [[Flamtaer hammer]] and a few Flamtaer bracelets it's possible to build the temple solo.

Alchemical hydra heads (mounted).name: Alchemical hydra heads (mounted)
Alchemical hydra heads (mounted).description: Players must complete [[Priest in Peril]] to be able to [[Taxidermist|stuff]] the [[alchemical hydra heads]]. If players remove the mounted head, they will receive nothing back.

Expeditious bracelet.name: Expeditious bracelet
Expeditious bracelet.description: When worn, the bracelet provides a 25% chance for a monster killed to count as two kills toward the player's [[Slayer task]] without granting additional experience. The use of this is to speed up Slayer tasks the player does not particularly like doing. Note that the bracelet needs to be worn '''only''' at the moment you defeat your opponent for the effect to occur, so for the rest of the fight, players may wear other bracelets or gloves such as [[Barrows gloves]].

Ketla the Unworthy.name: Ketla the Unworthy
Ketla the Unworthy.description: Ketla's shadow clones have a max hit of 7 through [[Protect from Missiles]]. As such, it is suggested to have armour with high ranged defence in order to preserve supplies for the next two fights. Shortly after summoning shadow clones, a skull will appear above her (similar to a player casting [[Vengeance]]), indicating the oncoming charged shot. Quickly move behind a shadow clone, and the shot will hit them instead.

Burnt bones.name: Burnt bones
Burnt bones.description: It is not recommended to train prayer with burnt bones, as they are no different from regular [[bones]], which are much easier to obtain.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Zu.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Zulrah Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Zu.description: The '''Zulrah Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Zulrah]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Curved bone.name: Curved bone
Curved bone.description: Curved bones may be sold to [[Barlak]], a [[Dorgesh-Kaan]] cave goblin, for 2,000 [[coins]] each. Dorgesh-Kaan can be accessed after the quest [[Death to the Dorgeshuun]]. The player will also be given a lecture on [[Construction]], granting 6,750 Construction [[experience]], as long as their Construction level is at least 30. If the player were to gain the same amount of experience by oak planks, it would cost them {{Coins|floor(6750/60*{{GEP|Oak plank}})}}, which can be considered as an extra theoretical value of a curved bone. '''Handing in bones does NOT grant any experience if you are under 30 Construction.'''

Altar (Sophanem).name: Altar (Sophanem)
Altar (Sophanem).description: A similar, broken altar can be found in the [[Temple of the Lesser Gods]] near [[Jex]]. This altar cannot be used to recharge prayer points until it is repaired after completion of [[Contact!]].

Magical melee.name: Magical melee
Magical melee.description: '''Note: '''Certain [[special attack]]s of melee weapons can deal a magical-melee attack (the [[Saradomin sword]] for example).

Amulet of defence.name: Amulet of defence
Amulet of defence.description: Amulets of defence can be sold to [[Davon's Amulet Store]] in [[Brimhaven]], starting at 1,147 coins each if none are in stock. The [[amulet of defence (t)]], a cosmetic variant, can be obtained as a rare reward from [[beginner clue scroll]]s.

Combat bracelet.name: Combat bracelet
Combat bracelet.description: A combat bracelet can be recharged at the [[Totem Pole (Legends' Guild)|totem pole]] in the [[Legends' Guild]], or at the [[Fountain of Uhld]] in the [[Myths' Guild]], giving it four charges. Players who have completed [[Legends' Quest]] can also recharge it at the [[Fountain of Rune]], giving it six charges, or by casting [[Recharge Dragonstone]], giving it four charges.

Ultor icon.name: Ultor icon
Ultor icon.description: The icon must be brought to a [[furnace]], alongside three [[chromium ingot]]s and a [[ring mould]], to craft the [[ultor ring]]. The entire process requires level 90 [[Magic]] and 80 [[Crafting]], which can be boosted.

Ensouled ogre head.name: Ensouled ogre head
Ensouled ogre head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Burning amulet.name: Burning amulet
Burning amulet.description: When rubbed, the amulet can teleport the player to various locations in the [[Wilderness]]; players will be given a warning before teleporting. After all five charges are used, the amulet will disintegrate.

Big bones.name: Big bones
Big bones.description: Big bones are also used to charge teleports on the [[giantsoul amulet]], with each set of big bones and a law rune providing one teleport charge. Players can exchange excess amulets for 30 bones by speaking to the [[Odd Old Man]] with the amulets in their inventory.

Kharyrll teleport (tablet).name: Kharyrll teleport (tablet)
Kharyrll teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Ancient)|ancient lectern]] by the altar inside the [[Ancient Pyramid]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 2 [[law rune]]s, and 1 [[blood rune]], as well as level 66 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Ancient Magicks]] spellbook.

Skeleton bonemeal.name: Skeleton bonemeal
Skeleton bonemeal.description: In order to bring the bones out of the dungeon to crush, players must [[die]] and reclaim the items from [[Death (NPC)|Death]].

Blessed gold bowl.name: Blessed gold bowl
Blessed gold bowl.description: The player must make the gold bowl by using two [[gold bar]]s and a [[hammer]] at an anvil while holding the [[sketch]] given to the player by Gujuo to make a [[gold bowl]]. The bowl can then be taken back to Gujuo to be blessed (must have 42 prayer points, however they will not be consumed), to make it ready for it to hold the holy water needed to free [[Ungadulu]]. It is possible to fail when blessing the bowl causing the player to lose 5 prayer points in the process. If the blessed bowl is filled with the sacred pure water of the [[Kharazi Jungle|Kharazi]] water pool, it becomes a [[golden bowl]] containing sacred pure water that can be used with an [[enchanted vial]] to make a vial of [[holy water]]: one bowl can fill up to 10 vials. After making one successful golden bowl, the player can smith a gold bowl at any anvil, without need of the sketch, for 30 [[Smithing]] experience (though there remains a chance of failure); the bowl can then be taken to Gujuo to have it blessed.

Jogre bones.name: Jogre bones
Jogre bones.description: They can be lit with a [[tinderbox]] at level 30 [[Firemaking]] to make [[burnt jogre bones]], granting 90 Firemaking experience. Burnt jogre bones are used with [[karambwanji paste]] during the [[Tai Bwo Wannai Trio]] [[Quests|quest]] to make [[marinated j' bones]].

Strength.name: Strength
Strength.description: When fighting in the aggressive stance, <math>4 * x</math> Strength experience is granted per hit, where <math>x</math> is the amount of damage dealt. Fighting using the controlled stance, however, grants <math>1.33 * x</math> Strength experience per hit, where <math>x</math> is the amount of damage dealt. For example, a player who hits a 1 would receive 4 Strength experience when fighting in the aggressive stance and 1.33 Strength experience when fighting in the controlled stance. The amount of experience received when fighting in the controlled stance is calculated in the same way that experience awarded to the [[Hitpoints]] skill is calculated.

Exchange:Trailblazer reloaded relic hunt.name: Exchange:Trailblazer reloaded relic hunter (t3) armour set

Redeyes' bone.name: Redeyes' bone
Redeyes' bone.description: The bone is to be buried in [[Yu'biusk]], in which Redeyes' soul will be freed and 10,000 [[Prayer]] experience is given. The experience is not affected by [[chewed bones]]' effect. If players attempt to bury it anywhere else, a message in the chatbox will state: {{mes|You should go to Yu'biusk before you bury this bone.}}

Venom.name: Venom
Venom.description: [[Zulrah]] and its [[snakeling]]s, [[Vorkath]], [[Araxxor]] and its [[araxyte]]s, [[Cursed Baboon|cursed baboon]]s, [[manticore]]s and [[Spider (Ungael)|spiders]] in the [[Ungael]] laboratory are the only monsters able to inflict venom. Manticores only inflict venom when the '''Mantimayhem''' tier 2 or 3 handicap is active. Players are able to inflict venom upon their enemies by using [[Venom#Weaponry that can inflict venom|certain weaponry]].

Steel bar.name: Steel bar
Steel bar.description: Currently, smelting a steel bar yields a profit of {{Coins|{{GEP|Steel bar}}-({{GEP|Iron ore}} + {{GEP|Coal|2}}) }}. For [[Free-to-play|free players]] or [[members]] without a [[coal bag]], the most bars one can smith at a time is 9, achieved with an inventory of 18 coal and 9 iron ore.

Altar (Arceuus).name: Altar (Arceuus)
Altar (Arceuus).description: According to [[Mofina]], the [[Citizens of Arceuus]] have moved beyond the need to pay the gods homage,{{CiteNPC|npc=Mofina|quote=While the gods are useful for tedious matters such as granting prayers during combat, we of Arceuus have long moved beyond the need to pay them homage.}} though they give permission to use the church to worship any god.{{CiteNPC|npc=Mofina|quote=Saradomin is popular with many uneducated citizens of Kourend, but you may use our church to worship any god you prefer. That would be an ecumenical matter.}}

Aggressiveness.name: Aggressiveness
Aggressiveness.description: Some monsters, such as [[chompies]] and [[jubblies]], will not attack a player even if engaged in [[combat]]. Yet, others, most notably [[dark beast]]s and bosses, remain hostile no matter how long the player remains in the vicinity.

Snothead's bone.name: Snothead's bone
Snothead's bone.description: The bone is to be buried in [[Yu'biusk]], in which Snothead's soul will be freed and 1,250 [[Prayer]] experience is given. The experience is not affected by [[chewed bones]]' effect. If players attempt to bury it anywhere else but Yu'biusk, a message in the chatbox will state {{mes|You should go to Yu'biusk before you bury this bone.}}

Saradomin altar.name: Saradomin altar
Saradomin altar.description: Praying at the altar will fully restore your [[prayer]] and give a +1 prayer bonus for every piece of equipment affiliated to [[Saradomin]]. After praying at the altar, you cannot pray at it again for 10 minutes; players can attempt to pray at the altar to see how much time they have left.

Magic pyre logs.name: Magic pyre logs
Magic pyre logs.description: Once the sacred oil has been obtained players will need to use four doses of it on one [[magic logs]]. These logs will then become one '''magic pyre logs''' and the player will be granted 20 Firemaking experience.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ch.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Chambers of Xeric Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ch.description: The '''Chambers of Xeric Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Chambers of Xeric]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 19 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Spectral spirit shield.name: Spectral spirit shield
Spectral spirit shield.description: The '''spectral spirit shield''' is a shield which requires 75 [[Defence]], 70 [[Prayer]] and 65 [[Magic]] to wield.

Ensouled aviansie head.name: Ensouled aviansie head
Ensouled aviansie head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sa.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sarachnis Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sa.description: The '''Sarachnis Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Sarachnis]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Deviant spectre.name: Deviant spectre
Deviant spectre.description: Directly east of the {{fairycode|djr}} [[fairy ring]] there is a mysterious hole for quick access to one of the locations of this creature (it must have been accessed earlier from below - ‘Climb-up Vine’ - if not there is a boulder instead of a Hole).

Attack types.name: Attack types
Attack types.description: *'''Slash''': Weapons that use slash as a primary attack type are [[longsword]]s, [[scimitar]]s, [[two-handed sword]]s, [[battleaxe]]s, [[axe]]s, [[abyssal whip]] and [[halberd]]s. [[Sword]]s, [[spear]]s and [[dagger]]s also use slash as a secondary attack type. Slash is best used against opponents wearing clothing or leather-based armour, or opponents with no armour at all. However, it is less effective in battles where opponent is wearing tough, usually metal [[armour]], or has scaly skin, e.g. dragons.

Ape atoll teleport (tablet).name: Ape atoll teleport (tablet)
Ape atoll teleport (tablet).description: Players with level 90 [[Magic]] can create this item on the [[Lectern (Arceuus)|Arceuus lectern]] in the [[Ouditor]]'s house if they have the [[Arceuus spellbook]] enabled. This requires 2 [[law rune]]s, 2 [[soul rune]]s, 2 [[blood rune]]s, and a [[dark essence block]] instead of the [[soft clay]] required for most magic tablets. Making the tablet grants 100 Magic experience, the same as casting the Ape Atoll Teleport spell. It is '''not''' required to have [[Monkey Madness I]] completed in order to make a tablet.

Leather.name: Leather
Leather.description: A single piece of leather can be found on top of a table in the [[Shayzien Encampment]]. You must use telekinetic grab to pick it up.

Shrine.name: Shrine
Shrine.description: Players can offer [[bird's egg]]s to the shrine to receive 100 [[Prayer]] experience and a [[bird nest]] with seeds or a piece of the [[evil chicken outfit]]. Eggs are offered automatically once every 4 [[ticks]], allowing for offering 1000 eggs per hour including banking.

Vile ashes.name: Vile ashes
Vile ashes.description: The [[ash sanctifier]] will automatically purify these [[Remains#Demonic ashes|demonic ashes]] for 12.5 experience if the [[Hard Kourend & Kebos Diary]] has been completed and 25 experience if the [[Elite Kourend & Kebos Diary]] is completed.

Ensouled tzhaar head.name: Ensouled tzhaar head
Ensouled tzhaar head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Ensouled dog head.name: Ensouled dog head
Ensouled dog head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ne.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Nex Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ne.description: The '''Nex Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Nex]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 29 April 2022, at an index of 100.

Guide Prices.name: Guide Prices
Guide Prices.description: The guide price consists of a small window in which an item from the inventory can be added or removed, while actively displaying the total and individual current [[Grand Exchange]] market price of each item(s). The prices of up to 28 different items can be checked in this interface. If a player clicks an untradeable item or attempts to price check a members item on a free to play world, text then appears, stating: ''"You cannot trade that item"''.

Bearded gorilla bones.name: Bearded gorilla bones
Bearded gorilla bones.description: [[Zooknock]] is able to make a [[bearded gorilla greegree]] with the bones in the Ape Atoll Dungeon. If players want to make a [[gorilla greegree]], they must use [[gorilla bones]] instead. After completion of [[Monkey Madness II]], players no longer need to bring bones; they can simply claim the greegree from [[Zooknock]] in the [[Tree Gnome Stronghold]].

Enchant ruby or topaz.name: Enchant ruby or topaz
Enchant ruby or topaz.description: This tablet can be made regardless of the player's current spell book. Using a [[staff of fire]] or [[lava battlestaff]] can reduce the costs of casting the spell.

Banner (Zamorak).name: Banner (Zamorak)
Banner (Zamorak).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to make the Zamorak banner. Sir Renitee will not assign a crest unless the player has over level 16 [[Construction]]. Players can use a Banner easel in another player's house if they do not have one.

Monster killing.name: Monster killing
Monster killing.description: Some monsters, particularly higher-levelled ones, are [[aggressive]], meaning they attack on sight of a player (such as [[deadly red spider]]s). Monsters will no longer be [[aggressive]] to players with a combat level of one more than twice the level of the monster in question. However, there are certain monsters that will never become [[tolerant]], such as [[Flesh Crawler]]s and [[Catablepon]].

Exchange:Raging echoes relic hunter (t2).name: Exchange:Raging echoes relic hunter (t2) armour set

Aberrant spectre.name: Aberrant spectre
Aberrant spectre.description: [[Deviant spectre]]s, found in the [[Catacombs of Kourend]], can be killed in their place if you are assigned aberrant spectres.

Revenant cyclops.name: Revenant cyclops
Revenant cyclops.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

Ensouled goblin head.name: Ensouled goblin head
Ensouled goblin head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Phrin remains.name: Phrin remains
Phrin remains.description: To burn the phrin remains, the player needs some pyre logs (see table for more info) and a [[tinderbox]]. First place the pyre logs on a [[Funeral Pyre|funeral pyre]], followed by the phrin remains, then light the pyre. This will grant the player [[Firemaking]] and [[Prayer]] experience (see table). Once burned, a bronze or steel [[shade key]], or some [[coins]], will appear next to the pyre. The keys can be used to either enter the catacombs or open the corresponding coloured doors to chests containing valuable items.

Wyrm bones.name: Wyrm bones
Wyrm bones.description: Burying them while wearing a [[dragonbone necklace]] will restore 3 prayer points.

Reanimated horror.name: Reanimated horror
Reanimated horror.description: Even though the head is dropped by both [[jungle horror]]s and [[cave horror]]s, the reanimated creature counts '''only''' towards jungle horror [[Slayer task]]s. They '''do not''' count as cave horrors, and similarly, a [[witchwood icon]] is '''not required''' to kill them.

Elidinis' ward (f).name: Elidinis' ward (f)
Elidinis' ward (f).description: The ward is fortified by attaching an [[arcane sigil]] to [[Elidinis' ward]], requiring level 90 [[Prayer]], 90 [[Smithing]], and 10,000 [[soul rune]]s, granting 260 experience in both skills in the process. Boosts can be used for the Prayer and Smithing level requirements to fortify the ward; players cannot pay [[Abbot Langley]] to fortify it for them, though he can remove the sigil from an arcane spirit shield. Upon fortifying Elidinis' ward, the chatbox states "''You fuse your Arcane sigil to Elidinis' ward, returning it to its former glory."''

Vampyre Juvinate.name: Vampyre Juvinate
Vampyre Juvinate.description: Alternatively, if you don't have an Ivandis flail, you can lower the health of a juvinate enough for it to flee. This way, you will not have to use a charge on your Rod of Ivandis. When a juvinate reaches about 1/3 health, they will disappear and turn into a cloud of mist and say "Ha, ha, ha, time to disappear and rejuvenate!"

Kasonde the Craven.name: Kasonde the Craven
Kasonde the Craven.description: For his explosion attack, he will perform from one to three shockwaves in succession, but there will be a small section close to him where players  can stand safely. As his potions will not disappear on the ground, it is important that these do not build up near the centre, or there will be no room to avoid Kasonde's explosions, which deal typeless damage in the low 30s.

Ensouled kalphite head.name: Ensouled kalphite head
Ensouled kalphite head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Ensouled dragon head.name: Ensouled dragon head
Ensouled dragon head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Riyl remains.name: Riyl remains
Riyl remains.description: To burn the riyl remains, the player needs [[willow pyre logs]] or better and a [[tinderbox]]. First place the pyre logs on a [[Funeral Pyre|funeral pyre]], followed by the riyl remains, then light the pyre. This will grant the player [[Firemaking]] and [[Prayer]] experience (see table). Once burned, a steel or black [[shade key]], or some [[coins]], will appear next to the pyre. The keys can be used to either enter the catacombs or open the corresponding coloured doors to chests containing valuable items.

Altar (Ferox Enclave).name: Altar (Ferox Enclave)
Altar (Ferox Enclave).description: On [[beta world]]s, the altar is replaced by a [[altar (unrestricted world)|different variant]] where players can also change their [[spellbook#Changing spellbooks|spellbook]].

Dragonfire.name: Dragonfire
Dragonfire.description: There are varying levels and tiers of dragonfire depending on the dragon in question. Standard dragons (such as common [[chromatic dragons]] and [[lava dragon]]s), use plain dragonfire, which can be mostly reduced with [[Protect from Magic]], and only use it in melee distance; thus, if the dragon is not able to attack the player, then it will be unable to use its dragonfire. If they are able to attack with melee, there is a 1/6 chance they may use it instead of a melee attack.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1755605769029075288|date=8 February 2024|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/XaxxA|archivedate=16 February 2024}} Baby dragons are incapable of using dragonfire.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Vo.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Vorkath Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Vo.description: The '''Vorkath Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Vorkath]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Gold bar.name: Gold bar
Gold bar.description: Apart from jewellery, gold bars can be used to create [[gold helmet]]s, used in the [[Between a Rock...]] quest, and [[gold bowl]]s which are used in the [[Legends' Quest]].

Altar (Myths' Guild).name: Altar (Myths' Guild)
Altar (Myths' Guild).description: Completion of the [[Dragon Slayer II]] [[quest]] is required to enter the guild and use the altar.

Altar (Ancient Pyramid).name: Altar (Ancient Pyramid)
Altar (Ancient Pyramid).description: After the completion of Desert Treasure I, players can use the shortcut from the south side of the pyramid to directly access the altar.

Bellator icon.name: Bellator icon
Bellator icon.description: The icon must be brought to a [[furnace]], alongside three [[chromium ingot]]s and a [[ring mould]], to craft the [[bellator ring]]. The entire process requires level 90 [[Magic]] and 80 [[Crafting]], which can be boosted.

Tree spirit (Lost City).name: Tree spirit (Lost City)
Tree spirit (Lost City).description: It is also considered a [[ghost]] for the purposes of a [[Slayer task]]. It can be fought in the [[Nightmare Zone]] after the quest is complete, but will not count towards a ghost task. It is not affected by any variation of the [[Salve amulet]].

Bellator ring.name: Bellator ring
Bellator ring.description: The ring requires level 90 [[Magic]] and 80 [[Crafting]] to create (both being boostable), as well as having learnt how to combine Fremennik ring icons with ancient vestiges via [[Peer the Seer]].

Bronze bar.name: Bronze bar
Bronze bar.description: [[Members]] can purchase bronze bars [[Shantay Pass Shop]] at the [[Shantay Pass]] south of [[Al Kharid]] for 8gp each or from [[Jiminua's Jungle Store]] north of [[Tai Bwo Wannai]] village for 12gp each.

Persten the Deceitful.name: Persten the Deceitful
Persten the Deceitful.description: She will also conjure a [[Portal (wighted leech)|portal]] that has 30 Hitpoints, which spawns [[Wighted Leech|wighted leeches]] until destroyed. She can create two at a time, and they will always be near the entrance of the room. The wighted leeches have 5 Hitpoints and move at a speed slower than walking, but attack at the same speed as darts on rapid style and have 100% accuracy, usually hitting between 4 and 6 that cannot be blocked by prayer.

Small ninja monkey bones.name: Small ninja monkey bones
Small ninja monkey bones.description: [[Zooknock]] is able to make a [[monkey greegree (small ninja)|small ninja monkey greegree]] with the bones in the Ape Atoll Dungeon. If players want to make a [[monkey greegree (medium ninja)|medium ninja monkey greegree]], they must use [[medium ninja monkey bones]] instead. After completion of [[Monkey Madness II]], players no longer need to bring bones; they can simply claim the greegree from [[Zooknock]] in the [[Tree Gnome Stronghold]].

Revenant ork.name: Revenant ork
Revenant ork.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

Moonclan teleport (tablet).name: Moonclan teleport (tablet)
Moonclan teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Lunar)|lunar lectern]] in the ceremonial building on [[Lunar Isle]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 1 [[law rune]], 2 [[earth rune]]s, and 2 [[astral rune]]s, as well as level 69 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Lunar spellbook]].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Re.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Revenant Maledictus Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Re.description: The '''Revenant Maledictus Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Revenant Maledictus]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 11 October 2024, at an index of 100.

Watchtower teleport (tablet).name: Watchtower teleport (tablet)
Watchtower teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on a [[mahogany eagle lectern|mahogany eagle]] or [[marble lectern]] as long as they have 2 [[law rune]]s, 2 [[earth rune]]s, 1 [[soft clay]] and level 58 [[Magic]], and completion of the Watchtower quest. [[Elemental staves]] can be substituted for runes and are recommended when making teleport tablets in large amounts at a time.

Strongbones' bone.name: Strongbones' bone
Strongbones' bone.description: The bone is to be buried in [[Yu'biusk]], in which Strongbones' soul will be freed and 20,000 [[Prayer]] experience is given. The experience is not affected by [[chewed bones]]' effect. If players attempt to bury it anywhere else but Yu'biusk, a message in the chatbox will state {{mes|You should go to Yu'biusk before you bury this bone.}}

Revenant demon.name: Revenant demon
Revenant demon.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

Arctic pyre logs.name: Arctic pyre logs
Arctic pyre logs.description: Once the sacred oil has been obtained players will need to use two doses of it upon some [[Arctic pine logs]]. These logs will then become Arctic pine pyre logs.

Obelisk of Air.name: Obelisk of Air
Obelisk of Air.description: As the Air obelisk is in the Wilderness, caution should be taken when visiting it due to [[player killing]], and an unprepared charger can end up losing their orbs and runes. Bringing teleport items such as an [[amulet of glory]] or runes may be wise, although one still has to be careful, since players with a high Magic level may [[Teleport Block|teleblock]] you.

Altar (Clan Hall).name: Altar (Clan Hall)
Altar (Clan Hall).description: An '''altar''' can be found inside the [[Clan Hall]], in the small chapel in the south-eastern corner of the hall. Like most [[altar]]s, this altar can be used to recharge [[prayer]] points.

Combat triangle.name: Combat triangle
Combat triangle.description: *The warrior's [[Armour/Melee armour|armour]] is most effective against [[ranged]] projectiles, as long as they can get close to a ranger. The warrior's armour is worse than useless against [[magic]], thus removing metal armour and using ranged armour instead while closing in on the mage, the tables are turned.

Ankou.name: Ankou
Ankou.description: Ankou are popular monsters for their common [[death rune|death]] and [[blood rune]] drops. They can be assigned as Slayer tasks by [[Vannaka]], [[Nieve]]/[[Steve]], [[Krystilia]], [[Duradel]]/[[Kuradal]], and [[Konar quo Maten]].

Dodgy necklace.name: Dodgy necklace
Dodgy necklace.description: While equipped, the necklace provides a 25% chance to prevent the player from being [[Stun (status)|stunned]] and damaged while [[pickpocketing]] [[NPC]]s. The necklace begins with 10 charges; one charge is consumed each time the necklace successfully prevents damage. When the last charge is consumed, the necklace crumbles to dust. This stacks multiplicatively with the spell [[Shadow Veil]], where Shadow Veil will attempt to avoid the stun first for a total of 36.25% chance to not take damage from a failed pickpocket. As the player cannot fail a pickpocket attempt on a knocked out NPC, damage taken during [[Thieving training#Levels 45-55/91: Blackjacking|blackjacking]] can only be received by failing a knockout; as such, a dodgy necklace will have no effect on blackjacking.

Shade.name: Shade
Shade.description: Shades are [[undead]] and thus affected by the [[Salve amulet]] and [[Crumble Undead]]. Unlike the [[Shades (Shades of Mort'ton)|shades]] of [[Mort'ton]], however, they are are '''not''' vulnerable to the [[Gadderhammer]].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Me.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Metal Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Me.description: The '''Metal Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current metals listed in the [[Market Watch]], with the starting date of this average on 13 June 2020, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of metal prices is reflected in this index.

Reanimated aviansie.name: Reanimated aviansie
Reanimated aviansie.description: Killing the creature will grant the player 1,234 Prayer XP. Just like its living form, this creature is immune to melee attacks, although they only attack with melee rather than ranged.

Ring of wealth.name: Ring of wealth
Ring of wealth.description: The price difference between a fully charged ring and an uncharged one is {{NoCoins|{{GEP|Ring of wealth (5)}}-{{GEP|Ring of wealth}}|c}}, so each charge costs about {{NoCoins|({{GEP|Ring of wealth (5)}}-{{GEP|Ring of wealth}})/5 round 0|c}}.

Catherby teleport (tablet).name: Catherby teleport (tablet)
Catherby teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Lunar)|lunar lectern]] in the ceremonial building on [[Lunar Isle]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 3 [[law rune]]s, 10 [[water rune]]s, and 3 [[astral rune]]s, as well as level 87 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Lunar spellbook]].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ba.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Barrows Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ba.description: The '''Barrows Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Barrows]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 19 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Degradation.name: Degradation
Degradation.description: Many items have the charge amount as part of their name; those that do not give the charges remaining (often as a percentage) using the ''Check-charges'' right-click option for the item.

Unarmed.name: Unarmed
Unarmed.description: In [[melee]] combat, unarmed fighting is possible through the unarmed fighting styles listed below. Most [[combat spells]] can be cast without weapon equipped, making [[Magic]] a strong option for encounters where no weapons are used. [[Ranged]] combat is not possible without weapon, as every ranged projectile either needs to be equipped in the weapon slot, or launched from a ranged weapon.

Spellbook.name: Spellbook
Spellbook.description: It is possible to switch between spellbooks by visiting altars associated with those spellbooks, with the standard spellbook being accessible at the [[Ancient Pyramid]] altar, [[Astral Altar]], and [[Tyss]] near the [[Dark Altar]]. It is often most efficient to utilize [[player-owned house altars]].

Medium ninja monkey bones.name: Medium ninja monkey bones
Medium ninja monkey bones.description: [[Zooknock]] is able to make a [[monkey greegree (medium ninja)|medium ninja monkey greegree]] with the bones in the Ape Atoll Dungeon. If players want to make a [[monkey greegree (small ninja)|small ninja monkey greegree]], they must use [[small ninja monkey bones]] instead. After completion of [[Monkey Madness II]], players no longer need to bring bones; they can simply claim the greegree from [[Zooknock]] in the [[Tree Gnome Stronghold]].

Carrallanger teleport (tablet).name: Carrallanger teleport (tablet)
Carrallanger teleport (tablet).description: Because this tablet teleports players to the Wilderness, a warning will appear upon clicking the "Break" option on the tablet. This can be toggled by right-clicking the "Configure" option.

Revenant knight.name: Revenant knight
Revenant knight.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

Amulet of torture.name: Amulet of torture
Amulet of torture.description: As a purely offensive amulet, it gives the second highest melee attack and strength bonuses of any [[neck slot]] item, outclassed only by the [[amulet of rancour]], where the amulet of torture is used in its creation.

Arcane spirit shield.name: Arcane spirit shield
Arcane spirit shield.description: It is made by attaching an [[arcane sigil]], a rare drop from the [[Corporeal Beast]], to a [[blessed spirit shield]] using a [[hammer]] at an [[anvil]]; this process requires 90 [[Prayer]] and 85 [[Smithing]]. Players without the required skill levels to create the shield may ask [[Abbot Langley]] in the [[Edgeville Monastery]] to combine the sigil and the blessed spirit shield, for a fee of 1,500,000 coins.

Ring of dueling.name: Ring of dueling
Ring of dueling.description: Each charge costs {{NoCoins|{{GEP|Ring of dueling(8)|0.125}}}} [[coins]] if all 8 charges are used, {{NoCoins|({{GEP|Ring of dueling(8)}}+{{GEP|Nature rune}}-765)/7}} if using High Level Alchemy (as described below), or {{NoCoins|({{GEP|Ring of dueling(8)}}+{{GEP|Nature rune}}-510)/7}} if using [[Low Level Alchemy]]. Alternatively, [[Explorer's ring]] can be used 30 times per day for a cost of {{NoCoins|({{GEP|Ring of dueling(8)}}-510)/7}}. This is viable if fewer than 210 charges are used on average each day, though it gives no Magic experience.

Primordial boots.name: Primordial boots
Primordial boots.description: They can be created by using a [[primordial crystal]] with a pair of [[dragon boots]]. This process cannot be reversed, and requires level 60 in [[Runecraft]] and [[Magic]] (boosts cannot be used), granting 200 experience in both skills.

Annakarl teleport (tablet).name: Annakarl teleport (tablet)
Annakarl teleport (tablet).description: Because this tablet teleports players to the Wilderness, a warning will appear upon clicking the "Break" option on the tablet. This can be toggled by right-clicking the "Configure" option.

Arceuus library teleport (tablet).name: Arceuus library teleport (tablet)
Arceuus library teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Arceuus)|Arceuus lectern]] in the [[Ouditor]]'s house with 1 [[law rune]], 2 [[earth rune]]s, and at least level 6 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Arceuus spellbook]]. In addition, a [[dark essence block]] is required to substitute [[soft clay]].

Altar (Ancient Prison).name: Altar (Ancient Prison)
Altar (Ancient Prison).description: Praying at the altar will fully restore [[Prayer]]. If the player is wearing a Zarosian item, it will also restore [[hitpoints]], [[run energy]], and [[special attack]] energy. In addition, it will give a +1 prayer point boost for every piece of equipment aligned to Zaros. This can be only be done every ten minutes.

Dagannoth bones.name: Dagannoth bones
Dagannoth bones.description: Dagannoth bones cannot be turned into [[Peach|peaches]] via the [[Bones to Peaches]] spell.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Co.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Common Trade Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Co.description: While specialised for just watching common trade prices, it is set up to give a broad look at the Grand Exchange economy, and the divisor may be adjusted to include new items added by [[Jagex]] (see the [[RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/FAQ|FAQ]] for more information).

Revenant goblin.name: Revenant goblin
Revenant goblin.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ch.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Chaos Fanatic Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ch.description: The '''Chaos Fanatic Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Chaos Fanatic]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 23 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Lunar bar.name: Lunar bar
Lunar bar.description: During the quests, the best way to make lunar metal objects in the fastest possible manner is to use the [[Superheat Item]] spell, then head over to [[Seers' Village]] and use the lunar bars on the anvil there. However, this bar does not require a specific Smithing level to smelt.

Dharok the Wretched.name: Dharok the Wretched
Dharok the Wretched.description: Due to him being able to hit up to 57 at 1 hitpoint remaining,{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1303658779549016065|date=9 September 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/T8ltH|archivedate=9 September 2020}} it is '''strongly recommended''' to keep [[Protect from Melee]] active at all times. He uses slash attacks, although relying on armour should not be taken into account as Protect from Melee is advised. If a player runs out of [[Prayer]] points when fighting Dharok, it is advisable to retreat since he can hit high and a [[ring of life]] is very unlikely to activate.

Reanimated kalphite.name: Reanimated kalphite
Reanimated kalphite.description: It is worth noting that unlike most other reanimated monsters, reanimated kalphites '''are''' [[poison]]ous.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ki.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/King Black Dragon Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ki.description: The '''King Black Dragon Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[King Black Dragon]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 22 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Lovakite bar.name: Lovakite bar
Lovakite bar.description: It can be smelted with a [[Smithing]] level of 45.

Verac the Defiled.name: Verac the Defiled
Verac the Defiled.description: Despite being able to hit through [[Protect from Melee]], it is still recommended as it negates on average 75% of his attacks and when the set effect does activate, lowers his max hit from 23 to 15. Despite using a flail his attacks are stab type, so armour defensive against that is advised if not using Protect from Melee and taking hits from Verac. He can be seen as one of the most tedious Barrows brothers to deal with since he is the only brother who cannot be alleviated solely by protection prayers, possibly requiring [[food]] too.

Holy symbol.name: Holy symbol
Holy symbol.description: It has the third highest prayer bonus for an amulet in game (after god [[stole]]s and the [[dragonbone necklace]]). It is cheap, easy to obtain, and is commonly used in conjunction with [[Proselyte armour]] and other high prayer granting armour when using protect prayers as a form of defence while training.

Berserker necklace.name: Berserker necklace
Berserker necklace.description: Players can attach a [[Berserker necklace ornament kit]], obtained from [[Clue scroll (hard)|hard]] [[Treasure Trails]], to create a [[Berserker necklace (or)]]. This is only cosmetic, and does not affect the necklace's stat bonuses. It can be dismantled, returning the necklace and ornament kit.

Loar remains.name: Loar remains
Loar remains.description: Once burned, a bronze [[shade key]] or some [[coins]] will appear next to the pyre. The keys can be used either to enter the catacombs or to open the corresponding coloured doors to chests containing valuable items.

Earth orb.name: Earth orb
Earth orb.description: An earth orb can be used on a [[battlestaff]], requiring 58 [[Crafting]], yielding an [[earth battlestaff]] and 112.5 Crafting experience.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Fo.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Food Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Fo.description: The '''Food Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current foods listed in the [[Market Watch]], with the starting date of this average on 27 January 2017, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Magic potion.name: Magic potion
Magic potion.description: Using a magic potion temporarily raises the player's [[Magic]] level by 4.

Blessed spirit shield.name: Blessed spirit shield
Blessed spirit shield.description: This shield's stats are comparable to the stats of the [[Arcane spirit shield|arcane]] and [[spectral spirit shield]]. It differs only in lacking the higher magic attack and defence stats of the enhanced shields. This shield is a good choice for any player using [[melee]] because of its substantial defence bonuses and prayer bonus. Its crush defence bonus is also one point higher than that of a completely charged [[Dragonfire shield]]. Players who use [[Magic]] or [[Ranged]] may also find this shield useful due to its lack of negative stats.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Du.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Duke Sucellus Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Du.description: The '''Duke Sucellus Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Duke Sucellus]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 16 September 2024, at an index of 100.

Ring of forging.name: Ring of forging
Ring of forging.description: A newly-enchanted ring has 140 charges. Each time the player smelts an iron ore while wearing the ring, one charge is consumed; after all charges are consumed, the ring crumbles to dust. If the player auto-smelts more iron ores than the number of remaining charges, the smelting will stop once the ring crumbles. The number of charges is specific to the player, not the ring, so swapping, dropping, or alching rings before 140 charges are used will '''not''' reset the number of smelts the player has left before a ring breaks. Players can right-click a ring of forging to either "check" how many charges remain in it or "break" it and reset the next one they use to its maximum charges.

Zealot's boots.name: Zealot's boots
Zealot's boots.description: The boots grant a 1.25% chance to prevent various remains from being consumed whilst training [[Prayer]]; wearing the full set will increase this chance to 5%, and stacks with the bone-saving effect of the altar in the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|Chaos Temple]]. However, this does not apply at the [[Forthos Dungeon]]'s [[Sacred Bone Burner]], nor when casting [[Sinister Offering]].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/He.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Hespori Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/He.description: The '''Hespori Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Hespori]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Wolf bones.name: Wolf bones
Wolf bones.description: Wolf bones look very similar to regular [[bones]], except wolf bones are slightly more greyish in colour.

Infernal ashes.name: Infernal ashes
Infernal ashes.description: The [[ash sanctifier]] will automatically purify these [[Remains#Demonic ashes|demonic ashes]] for 55 experience if the [[Hard Kourend & Kebos Diary]] has been completed and 110 experience if the [[Elite Kourend & Kebos Diary]] is completed.

Angry barbarian spirit.name: Angry barbarian spirit
Angry barbarian spirit.description: These monsters are ''not'' considered to be [[undead]] (as indicated when trying to cast [[Crumble Undead]] on them), so a [[salve amulet]] or [[salve amulet (e)]] will not help.

Revenant hellhound.name: Revenant hellhound
Revenant hellhound.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Am.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Amoxliatl Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Am.description: The '''Amoxliatl Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Amoxliatl ]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 16 October 2024, at an index of 100.

Vampyre Juvenile.name: Vampyre Juvenile
Vampyre Juvenile.description: If a juvenile turns to mist, they will say "Ha, ha, ha, time to disappear and rejuvenate!" before disappearing. Juveniles cannot be killed by any means other than with a Guthix balance; even if they are reduced to 0 hitpoints, they will still turn to mist instead of dying.

Camelot teleport (tablet).name: Camelot teleport (tablet)
Camelot teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on a [[Teak eagle lectern]], a [[Mahogany eagle lectern]], or a [[Marble lectern|Marble Lectern]] as long as they have 1 [[law rune]], 5 [[air rune]]s, and 1 [[soft clay]] and at least level 45 [[Magic]], granting 55.5 experience. In addition to using air runes, a player may also use a [[staff of air]] to reduce the cost and allow for an extra inventory slot.

Ourg bones.name: Ourg bones
Ourg bones.description: Due to only being able to obtain them once from Slash Bash, and ogre coffins being slow to loot, Ourg bones are relatively rare, and as a result are generally much pricier than bones that provide similar Prayer experience. Unlike [[superior dragon bones]], they do not have a Prayer level requirement to offer them, and grant almost as much experience.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ka.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Kalphite Queen Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ka.description: The '''Kalphite Queen Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Kalphite Queen]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Enchanted ruby sickle (b).name: Enchanted ruby sickle (b)
Enchanted ruby sickle (b).description: The sickle has a right-click "bloom" option which can be used next to rotten logs, branches or bushes in [[Mort Myre]] swamp to obtain [[Mort myre fungi]], [[Mort myre stem|stems]] and [[Mort myre pear|pears]]. These items can be used to fill the [[Druid pouch]] which allows the player to fight [[Ghast]]s.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Co.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Corporeal Beast Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Co.description: The '''Corporeal Beast Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Corporeal Beast]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Cemetery teleport (tablet).name: Cemetery teleport (tablet)
Cemetery teleport (tablet).description: Because this tablet teleports players to the Wilderness, a warning will appear upon clicking the "Break" option on the tablet. This can be toggled by right-clicking the "Configure" option.

Venator ring.name: Venator ring
Venator ring.description: The ring requires level 90 [[Magic]] and 80 [[Crafting]] to create (both being boostable), as well as having learnt how to combine Fremennik ring icons with ancient vestiges via [[Peer the Seer]].

Ensouled scorpion head.name: Ensouled scorpion head
Ensouled scorpion head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Barbarian teleport (tablet).name: Barbarian teleport (tablet)
Barbarian teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Lunar)|lunar lectern]] in the ceremonial building on [[Lunar Isle]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 2 [[law rune]]s, 3 [[fire rune]]s, and 2 [[astral rune]]s, as well as level 75 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Lunar spellbook]].

Rune kiteshield (Guthix).name: Rune kiteshield (Guthix)
Rune kiteshield (Guthix).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to make the kiteshield. Players can use an easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Inoculation bracelet.name: Inoculation bracelet
Inoculation bracelet.description: When equipped, it protects the wearer a total of 275 [[disease]] damage. This includes the negative stat bonus "damage." Players still get diseased, but it reduces the damage normally taken from the disease to 0. It degrades to dust once its protection has been depleted. It may also be right-click operated to find out how much more protection it will provide.

Ensouled dagannoth head.name: Ensouled dagannoth head
Ensouled dagannoth head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Enchant onyx.name: Enchant onyx
Enchant onyx.description: This tablet can be made regardless of the player's current spell book.

Tortured soul.name: Tortured soul
Tortured soul.description: They count as ghosts for slayer tasks. They are vulnerable to [[Crumble Undead]]. It is possible to safespot them by hiding behind plants and fences.

West ardougne teleport (tablet).name: West ardougne teleport (tablet)
West ardougne teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Arceuus)|Arceuus lectern]] in the [[Ouditor]]'s house with 2 [[law rune]]s, 2 [[soul rune]]s, and level 61 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Arceuus spellbook]]. In addition, a [[dark essence block]] is required to substitute [[soft clay]].

Pile jumping.name: Pile jumping
Pile jumping.description: The abbreviaton '''PJing''' can also mean '''player jumping''' or '''player jacking''', which is attacking a player whose opponent is not dead yet.

Elemental weakness.name: Elemental weakness
Elemental weakness.description: For every percentage point of elemental weakness that an NPC has, the player will gain an extra 1% [[magic damage]] and 1% [[accuracy|magic accuracy]] to their attacks. The bonus to magic damage is added after all previous magic damage sources, such as equipment or bonuses from the [[Slayer helmet (i)]] or [[Salve amulet (i)]].

Fenkenstrain's castle teleport (tablet).name: Fenkenstrain's castle teleport (tablet)
Fenkenstrain's castle teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Arceuus)|Arceuus lectern]] in the [[Ouditor]]'s house with 1 [[law rune]], 1 [[earth rune]], 1 [[soul rune]], and level 48 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Arceuus spellbook]]. In addition, a [[dark essence block]] is required to substitute [[soft clay]].

Willow pyre logs.name: Willow pyre logs
Willow pyre logs.description: Once the sacred oil has been obtained players will need to use three doses of it upon some [[willow logs]]. These logs will then become willow pyre logs and grants 12 [[Firemaking]] experience.

Altar (Xeric).name: Altar (Xeric)
Altar (Xeric).description: Two '''Altars''' with a [[Xeric]]ian symbol can be found in the [[Kebos Swamp]]. One can be found in the [[Xeric's Shrine]] and one can be found in the settlement of [[Molch]]. Like with most [[altar]]s, players can recharge their [[prayer]] points here.

Blessed superior dragon bones.name: Blessed superior dragon bones
Blessed superior dragon bones.description: Unlike other types of blessed bones, blessed superior dragon bones require a [[Prayer]] level of 70 to be blessed at the exposed alter.

Silver bar.name: Silver bar
Silver bar.description: The primary use of a silver bar is to create [[jewellery]] with the [[Crafting]] skill. To craft silver bars into jewellery players must use a silver bar on a furnace with a proper [[mould]] in their inventory. If players wish to craft jewellery with [[gems]] inset, the cut gems must be present in the player's inventory before crafting the jewellery. One silver bar is used during the [[Creature of Fenkenstrain]] quest, and another during [[Shadow of the Storm]].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/He.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Herb Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/He.description: The '''Herb Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current herbs listed in the [[Market Watch]], with the starting date of this average on 13 June 2020, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of herb prices is reflected in this index.

Amoxliatl.name: Amoxliatl
Amoxliatl.description: After the quest, Amoxliatl can be fought again as a regular [[boss]]. Like [[Scurrius]], she is considered an entry-level boss with attacks meant to introduce various mechanics that are present in higher-level bosses, such as quickly reacting to prayers being deactivated and controlling where persistent ground hazards appear, which are comparable to [[Vorkath]]'s corrupting dragonfire and the [[Phantom Muspah]]'s ground spikes respectively.

Banner (Guthix).name: Banner (Guthix)
Banner (Guthix).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to make the Guthix banner. Sir Renitee will not assign a crest unless the player has over level 16 [[Construction]]. Players can use a Banner easel in another player's house if they do not have one.

Magic tablet.name: Magic tablet
Magic tablet.description: Making magic tablets requires that the player to have the appropriate [[Magic]] level and correct spellbook unlocked. Using them doesn't require either.

Molten glass.name: Molten glass
Molten glass.description: Molten glass is used in some quests such as [[Observatory Quest]], [[Horror from the Deep]], [[Wanted!]], [[Desert Treasure I]], [[Another Slice of H.A.M.]] and [[The Fremennik Exiles]]. Although you can't buy molten glass at any shop in the game, you can still buy buckets of sand and soda ash from the charter ship shops. This is especially useful for [[ironmen]], who could buy both items and then smelt them in a furnace.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Al.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Alchemical Hydra Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Al.description: The '''Alchemical Hydra Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Alchemical Hydra]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 22 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/So.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sol Heredit Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/So.description: The '''Sol Heredit Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Sol Heredit ]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 13 October 2024, at an index of 100.

Attack range.name: Attack range
Attack range.description: Players may use a weapon's attack range to their advantage to avoid retaliation by hiding behind objects or walls - such areas are known as [[safespot]]s, and this tactic is known as "safespotting", or "farcasting" when done with magic.

God Alignments.name: God Alignments
God Alignments.description: Details concerning how they're unlocked, as well as the specifics of what each prayer does, are not currently set in stone and are subject to change. The current proposal suggests that each set of prayers would be unlocked for completion of a corresponding [[grandmaster quest]], but it may be that completion of the quest may only unlock a portion of each alignment, and completion of additional content may be required.

Altar (Edgeville Monastery).name: Altar (Edgeville Monastery)
Altar (Edgeville Monastery).description: The '''Altar''' in the [[Edgeville Monastery]] is one of the many [[altar]]s dedicated to [[Saradomin]]. Praying at this altar recharges [[prayer]] points, and gives '''2 extra''' prayer points. A prayer level of 31 is required to reach the altar.

Tetra.name: Tetra
Tetra.description: Tetra can be obtained by preparing a [[raw tetra]] on the [[preparation table]] whilst having a [[knife]]. Preparing tetra requires level 33 [[Cooking]] and grants 31 cooking experience when successful. Players may ruin the tetra during preparation, resulting in a [[ruined tetra]]; the [[burn rate|chance of failure]] while preparing these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Gr.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Grotesque Guardians Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Gr.description: The '''Grotesque Guardians Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Grotesque Guardians]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 19 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Splashing/Guide.name: Splashing/Guide
Splashing/Guide.description: Despite the enemy remaining alive indefinitely, after 20 minutes the player will stop auto-retaliating. As a consequence, timely interaction with the game is needed to not be logged out due to inactivity.

Sapphire dragon bolts (e).name: Sapphire dragon bolts (e)
Sapphire dragon bolts (e).description: ''Clear Mind'' drains a portion of the target's [[Prayer points]] and grants them to the attacker. The chance of this effect occurring and amount drained varies when attacking [[Monsters]] or [[Players]]

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sc.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Scurrius Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sc.description: The '''Scurrius Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Scurrius]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 24 September 2024, at an index of 100.

Chapel.name: Chapel
Chapel.description: This room can be built with 45 [[Construction]] and {{Coins|50000}}.

Adamant kiteshield (Guthix).name: Adamant kiteshield (Guthix)
Adamant kiteshield (Guthix).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to make the kiteshield. Players can use an easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Zealot's robes.name: Zealot's robes
Zealot's robes.description: Because a single bone can be saved multiple times by this set, similar to the Chaos Temple altar, the set provides a 5.26% increase<ref>https://www.wolframalpha.com/input?i=Sum%5B20%5E%28-n%29%2C+%7Bn%2C+0%2C+Infinity%7D%5D</ref> in the average Prayer experience a player can expect.

Zealot's helm.name: Zealot's helm
Zealot's helm.description: The helmet grants a 1.25% chance to prevent various remains from being consumed whilst training [[Prayer]]; wearing the full set will increase this chance to 5%, and stacks with the bone-saving effect of the altar in the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|Chaos Temple]]. However, this does not apply at the [[Forthos Dungeon]]'s [[Sacred Bone Burner]], nor when casting [[Sinister Offering]].

Bow string.name: Bow string
Bow string.description: It takes approximately 50 seconds to spin a full [[inventory]] of 28 [[flax]], requiring 10 [[Crafting]] and granting a total of 420 [[experience]]. A conveniently located spinning wheel can be found on the middle floor of [[Lumbridge Castle]]. Including travel time, an inventory can be spun in approximately 75 seconds here, which equates to 48 inventories, 1344 bow string and just over 20,000 Crafting experience per hour.

Mine cart (Trahaearn mine).name: Mine cart (Trahaearn mine)
Mine cart (Trahaearn mine).description: Players can use this mine cart as a convenient way to deposit ores mined within the Trahaearn mine.

Enchant diamond.name: Enchant diamond
Enchant diamond.description: This tablet can be made regardless of the player's current [[spellbook]]. Using a [[Staff of earth]] can reduce the costs of casting the spell.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Br.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Bryophyta Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Br.description: The '''Bryophyta Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Bryophyta]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ve.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Vet'ion Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ve.description: The '''Vet'ion Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Vet'ion]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sc.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Scorpia Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sc.description: The '''Scorpia Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Scorpia]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 22 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Frost Nagua.name: Frost Nagua
Frost Nagua.description: As with their [[Sulphur Nagua|sulphurous counterparts]], Frost Nagua have -4 [[flat armour]], so all successful hits will do an extra 4 damage to them.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ce.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Cerberus Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ce.description: The '''Cerberus Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Cerberus]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 22 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Kq head.name: Kq head
Kq head.description: It can also be [[Kalphite Queen head (mounted)|mounted]] in a [[Skill Hall]] in a [[player-owned house]]. Before it can be mounted, it must be stuffed by the [[Taxidermist]] in [[Canifis]], where she will charge 50,000 coins and return a [[stuffed kq head]] to the player. They can then mount the head using 2 [[mahogany plank]]s and 2 [[gold leaf|gold leaves]]. When players take it to the Taxidermist, she will exclaim ''"That must be the biggest kalphite I've ever seen! Preserving insects is always tricky. I'll have to be careful..."''

Bones (Ape Atoll).name: Bones (Ape Atoll)
Bones (Ape Atoll).description: When players leave the dungeon with them in your inventory, a message will appear in the chatbox stating that "The skeleton bones you are carrying crumble to dust", and they turn into [[ashes]]. However, they can be safely smuggled out via [[dying]] and reclaiming the items from [[Death (NPC)|Death]].

Bleached bones.name: Bleached bones
Bleached bones.description: Players can bury bleached bones for 4.5 [[Prayer]] experience. Unlike [[long bone|long]] and [[curved bone]]s, there is no warning that prevents the players from accidentally burying the bones. Alternatively, players can turn bleached bones into [[bonemeal]] at the [[Ectofuntus]]. Bleached bones cannot be used on the [[Exposed altar]] in [[The Teomat]].

Blessed bone shards.name: Blessed bone shards
Blessed bone shards.description: To make sacrifices, the libation bowl must be filled with [[Jug of blessed wine|jugs of blessed wine]] or [[Jug of blessed sunfire wine|jugs of blessed sunfire wine]], and the player must have at least 2 [[Prayer points]] to perform it. The passive effect of [[Zealot's robes]] can be used to save some shards while sacrificing them. The chance to preserve material is calculated for each individual shard, rather than the entire set of 100 for every action taken.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ch.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Chaos Elemental Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ch.description: The '''Chaos Elemental Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Chaos Elemental]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 22 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Elysian spirit shield.name: Elysian spirit shield
Elysian spirit shield.description: It is made by attaching an [[elysian sigil]], a rare drop from the [[Corporeal Beast]], to a [[blessed spirit shield]] using a [[hammer]] at an [[anvil]]; this process requires 90 [[Prayer]] and 85 [[Smithing]]. Players without the required skill levels to create the shield may ask [[Abbot Langley]] in the [[Edgeville Monastery]] to combine the sigil and the blessed spirit shield, for a fee of 1,500,000 coins.

Kbd head (mounted).name: Kbd head (mounted)
Kbd head (mounted).description: Players must complete [[Priest in Peril]] to be able to [[Taxidermist|stuff]] the [[kbd heads]]. If players remove the mounted head, they will receive nothing back.

Yew pyre logs.name: Yew pyre logs
