Yew pyre logs.description: Once the sacred oil has been obtained players will need to use four doses of it upon some [[yew logs]]. These logs will then become Yew pyre logs and the player is granted 16 Firemaking experience.

Ring of stone.name: Ring of stone
Ring of stone.description: [[File:Ring of stone equipped.png|right|thumb|240px|Players take this form when the ring is active.]]

Hunter kit.name: Hunter kit
Hunter kit.description: These items are somewhat useful for beginning [[hunter]]s, but have very limited uses for experienced hunters due to the role of them in the skill.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Va.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Vardorvis Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Va.description: The '''Vardorvis Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Vardorvis ]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 13 October 2024, at an index of 100.

Urium Shade.name: Urium Shade
Urium Shade.description: As with all [[Shades (Shades of Mort'ton)|shades in Mort'ton]], Urium shades possess 2 traits you should be aware of:

Adamant heraldic helm (Guthix).name: Adamant heraldic helm (Guthix)
Adamant heraldic helm (Guthix).description: Players need level 70 [[Prayer]] in order to create the helm. Players can use a stand or easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Steel kiteshield (Zamorak).name: Steel kiteshield (Zamorak)
Steel kiteshield (Zamorak).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to create the kiteshield. Players can use an easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Item set.name: Item set
Item set.description: For each standard or trimmed metal armour set, there are two types of sets. One type, denoted by an "(lg)" suffix (meaning "legs"), contains a [[platebody]], [[platelegs]], [[full helmet]], and [[kiteshield]]. The other type, which has an "(sk)" suffix (meaning "skirt"), contains the same items, except the platelegs are substituted with a [[plateskirt]]. All other armour sets without separate leg and skirt pieces only have one variation.

Varrock teleport (tablet).name: Varrock teleport (tablet)
Varrock teleport (tablet).description: This tablet can be made regardless of the player's current [[spellbook]].

Guthan the Infested.name: Guthan the Infested
Guthan the Infested.description: Guthan is often regarded as one of the easier brothers since he is inaccurate compared to most of the other brothers. Although he attacks by stabbing with his warspear, Guthan's attacks are classified as [[crush]], so armour defensive against crush is advised. Despite his inaccuracy, he can still hit up to 24 so the use of [[Protect from Melee]] is advised for players with low [[Defence]]. Players who get hit often may also cause his set effect to activate more and thus he will heal more, making the fight longer. Using Protect from Melee also prevents his set effect from activating.

Remains.name: Remains
Remains.description: Bones can be buried, or offered to certain altars for more Prayer experience. Casting [[Sinister Offering]] on them also grants [[Magic]] experience. For the costs per bone and hourly experience rates, see the [[Calculator:Prayer/Bones|price calculator]] and [[Prayer training]] pages.

Revenant imp.name: Revenant imp
Revenant imp.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

Lassar teleport (tablet).name: Lassar teleport (tablet)
Lassar teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Ancient)|ancient lectern]] by the altar inside the [[Ancient Pyramid]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 2 [[law rune]]s, and 4 [[water rune]]s, as well as level 72 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Ancient Magicks]] spellbook.

Water orb.name: Water orb
Water orb.description: The Water Obelisk is located on the island across from the shore of [[Catherby]], getting there by climbing a ladder at the end of [[Taverley Dungeon]] by the [[black dragon]]s. Accessing this section of the dungeon requires the [[dusty key]] or 70 agility.

Vorkath's head (mounted).name: Vorkath's head (mounted)
Vorkath's head (mounted).description: If players remove the mounted head, they will receive nothing back.

Poison.name: Poison
Poison.description: '''Poison''' is a status effect that players and monsters suffer when they are attacked by a poisonous [[weapon]]. Many [[NPCs]] are able to inflict poison naturally, whilst players can use weapons laced with weapon poison (or [[smoke spells]] from the [[Ancient Magicks]]) to inflict poison. However, not all monsters can be inflicted with poison; a full list of monsters susceptible to poison can be found [[Concept:Monsters susceptible to poison|here]], whilst a list of monsters immune to poison can be found [[Concept:Monsters immune to poison|here]].

Free-to-play Magic training.name: Free-to-play Magic training
Free-to-play Magic training.description: At level 1 Magic, you'll only be able to cast [[Wind Strike]], which requires one [[air rune]] and one [[mind rune]]. With a [[staff of air]] equipped, you have access to unlimited air runes, so that you don't need air runes. There are staves for every basic type of rune; these staves are referred to as [[elemental staves]], and will help assist in training Magic and give you unlimited runes for that element.

Zealot's robe top.name: Zealot's robe top
Zealot's robe top.description: The robe top grants a 1.25% chance to prevent various remains from being consumed whilst training [[Prayer]]; wearing the full set will increase this chance to 5%, and stacks with the bone-saving effect of the altar in the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|Chaos Temple]]. However, this does not apply at the [[Forthos Dungeon]]'s [[Sacred Bone Burner]], nor when casting [[Sinister Offering]].

Revenant dark beast.name: Revenant dark beast
Revenant dark beast.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

Steel kiteshield (Guthix).name: Steel kiteshield (Guthix)
Steel kiteshield (Guthix).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to make the kiteshield. Players can use an easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Urium remains.name: Urium remains
Urium remains.description: To burn the urium remains, first place [[redwood pyre logs]] on a [[Funeral Pyre|funeral pyre]], followed by the urium remains, then light the pyre with a [[tinderbox]]. This will grant the player 500 [[Firemaking]] experience (750 with [[Morytania Diary#Elite|elite Morytania Diary]] complete) and 120.5 [[Prayer]] (180.7 with [[Morytania Diary#Hard|hard Morytania Diary]] complete) experience. Neither the [[pyromancer outfit]] nor [[zealot's robes]] increase Firemaking or Prayer experience gained from burning shade remains.

Babydragon bones.name: Babydragon bones
Babydragon bones.description: Using babydragon bones instead of [[dragon bones]] is a slower but cheaper method to gain Prayer experience.

Otherworldly being.name: Otherworldly being
Otherworldly being.description: More specifically, five of the six otherworldly beings have a [[wander radius]] which permits safespotting without having them [[retreat]] as long as the player stands right next to the pond. One of these five will retreat if attacked horizontally across the pond, and another will retreat when attacked vertically. The other three will not retreat as long as you stay next to the pond.

Safespot.name: Safespot
Safespot.description: This works because [[Non-player character|NPCs]], and some automatic [[player]] movements, always move directly toward their target and do not detour around obstacles if that would mean moving away. Larger monsters, such as [[dragons]], may also end up snagged on a corner, even if it looks like they do have an almost direct path.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/K'.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/K'ril Tsutsaroth Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/K'.description: The '''K'ril Tsutsaroth Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[K'ril Tsutsaroth]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Cavefish.name: Cavefish
Cavefish.description: Cavefish can be obtained by preparing a [[raw cavefish]] on the [[preparation table]] whilst having a [[knife]]. Preparing cavefish requires level 20 [[Cooking]] and grants 23 cooking experience when successful. Players may ruin the cavefish during preparation, resulting in a [[ruined cavefish]]; the [[burn rate|chance of failure]] while preparing these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels.

Riyl Shade.name: Riyl Shade
Riyl Shade.description: As with all [[Shades (Shades of Mort'ton)|shades in Mort'ton]], Riyl shades possess 2 traits you should be aware of:

Oak plank.name: Oak plank
Oak plank.description: A single oak plank is worth on average of ~175 experience when used in novice [[Mahogany Homes]] contracts (including completion bonus), and 150 experience when used to fix the [[Bridge (Hallowed Sepulchre)|broken bridges]] in the [[Hallowed Sepulchre]], also requiring [[mithril nails]].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/The Mimic Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.description: The '''The Mimic Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[The Mimic]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Ring of life.name: Ring of life
Ring of life.description: The ring does not guarantee total safety, as a player wearing one will still die if they are hit from above 10% of their maximum Hitpoints to zero (for example, being hit 15 while at 15 hitpoints), and it '''will not''' cure [[poison]]. Self-inflicted damage, such as guzzling a [[dwarven rock cake]] or using a [[locator orb]], can also activate the effect. If it is worn along with a [[phoenix necklace]], the necklace effect will trigger first. In [[Player killing|PvP]], the [[Tele Block]] spell will prevent a player's ring of life from activating. The teleport will work up to level 30 [[Wilderness]], as opposed to the normal limit of level 20 for most jewellery-based teleports below [[dragonstone]].

Ranged magic.name: Ranged magic
Ranged magic.description: ''Note:'' The monsters above are present in constant-combat environments in which you will also be taking other forms of damage (melee, ranged, traditional magic) - decide on equipment accordingly.

Binding necklace.name: Binding necklace
Binding necklace.description: Similar to a [[ring of recoil]], binding necklace charges are stored per player, not per necklace. Thus if the player sells or casts High Level Alchemy on a necklace with 1 charge remaining, the next necklace the player equips will still have only 1 charge. The player can right-click to "destroy" a binding necklace, destroying it and restoring the next binding necklace the player equips to 16 charges. This can be useful when a necklace drops to 1 charge left and a player is crafting runes in pairs, where a player can destroy a second necklace in their inventory and the equipped one will regain charges.

Battlefront teleport (tablet).name: Battlefront teleport (tablet)
Battlefront teleport (tablet).description: Players with 23 [[Magic]] and the [[Arceuus Spellbook|Arceuus spellbook]] enabled can create this item on the [[Lectern (Arceuus)|Arceuus lectern]] in the [[Ouditor]]'s house with 1 [[law rune]], 1 [[earth rune]], 1 [[fire rune]], and a [[dark essence block]] instead of the [[soft clay]] required for most magic tablets. This grants 19 Magic [[experience]].

Pegasian boots.name: Pegasian boots
Pegasian boots.description: They can be created by using a [[pegasian crystal]] with a pair of [[ranger boots]]. This process cannot be reversed, and requires level 60 in [[Runecraft]] and [[Magic]] (boosts cannot be used), granting 200 experience in both skills.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch.description: The [[Grand Exchange]] Prices can be found on the official website [http://services.runescape.com/m=itemdb_oldschool/ here]. The Old School Wiki's real-time price guide can be found [https://prices.runescape.wiki/osrs/ here].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ge.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/General Graardor Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ge.description: The '''General Graardor Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[General Graardor]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Bracelet of clay.name: Bracelet of clay
Bracelet of clay.description: A single bracelet can mine 28 [[soft clay]], after which it disintegrates. The player can check how many more soft clay it can mine by equipping it and then right-clicking "check." The number of charges is stored per player, not per bracelet, so equipping another bracelet will not reset the number of charges a player has.

Castle wars bracelet.name: Castle wars bracelet
Castle wars bracelet.description: When players are wielding this item at the moment they enter the game, they do an extra 20% damage against a bearer of a flag, and [[bandages]] heal 50% more. Players only need to be wearing it up until the time the game starts. After that, the charge is already given, and the player can switch to any item to be worn in the [[hand slot]].

Zealot's robe bottom.name: Zealot's robe bottom
Zealot's robe bottom.description: The robe bottom grants a 1.25% chance to prevent various remains from being consumed whilst training [[Prayer]]; wearing the full set will increase this chance to 5%, and stacks with the bone-saving effect of the altar in the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|Chaos Temple]]. However, this does not apply at the [[Forthos Dungeon]]'s [[Sacred Bone Burner]], nor when casting [[Sinister Offering]].

Bones to peaches (tablet).name: Bones to peaches (tablet)
Bones to peaches (tablet).description: The tablet is particularly useful for players who have not unlocked the spell, for players wishing to save inventory space by bringing them instead of the runes required to cast the spell, or for situations where another [[spellbook]] is more useful and would still want to cast Bones to Peaches.

Fiendish ashes.name: Fiendish ashes
Fiendish ashes.description: The [[Ash sanctifier]] will automatically purify these [[Remains#Demonic ashes|demonic ashes]] for 5 experience if the [[Hard Kourend & Kebos Diary]] has been completed and 10 experience if the [[Elite Kourend & Kebos Diary]] is completed. It is NOT recommended to use the Ash sanctifier on demonic creatures dropping these ashes as it is not cost effective.

Air orb.name: Air orb
Air orb.description: An air orb can be used on a [[battlestaff]], requiring 66 [[Crafting]], yielding an [[air battlestaff]] and 137.5 Crafting experience.

Calculator:Magic/Enchant jewellery.name: Calculator:Magic/Enchant jewellery
Calculator:Magic/Enchant jewellery.description: The '''jewellery enchantment calculator''' calculates the profit or loss of enchanting jewellery with the one of the six enchantment spells.

Combat.name: Combat
Combat.description: '''Combat''' is an event in ''[[RuneScape]]'' in which two or more characters and/or [[bestiary|monsters]] or [[NPCs]] fight.

Magus ring.name: Magus ring
Magus ring.description: The ring requires level 90 [[Magic]] and 80 [[Crafting]] to create (both being boostable), as well as having learnt how to combine Fremennik ring icons with ancient vestiges via [[Peer the Seer]].

Broken sun altar.name: Broken sun altar
Broken sun altar.description: Once players complete [[In Search of Knowledge]] and have used the [[temple coin]] on the [[stone relief]], they can speak to the [[Knight of Varlamore (Kourend Castle)|Knight of Varlamore]] and inform him about the dungeon; he will then be found by the broken sun altar. Once he is there, praying at the broken altar will result in a different animation rather than the standard praying animation.

Monster.name: Monster
Monster.description: While some monsters will never begin a fight with a player, many high level creatures are [[aggressive]], potentially causing unwanted death. If a player has over double the [[combat level]] of the monster, the monster will be docile, and will only attack when provoked. However, in areas such as the [[Wilderness]], most monsters are indefinitely aggressive. As a rule of thumb, "humanoids" are not aggressive towards players except in some cases when the humanoid's nature or occupation has malign or criminal connotations (i.e. [[Black Knight]], [[Zombie]], [[Mugger]]). Most cities are also safe from aggressive monsters, though the perimeter or surroundings may not be as secure.

Altar (Seren).name: Altar (Seren)
Altar (Seren).description: Like at most [[altar]]s, players can pray at them to recharge their [[prayer]] points.

Player killing.name: Player killing
Player killing.description: Currently, players can also participate in player killing in dedicated "PvP worlds," where players can attack other players in most places around [[Gielinor]], with the exception of designated safe areas and banks. There is only one dedicated PvP world that does not change with the [[Server#Player killing|PvP world rota]], this is World 392. Other worlds can be found on the [[server]] list.

Bracelet of slaughter.name: Bracelet of slaughter
Bracelet of slaughter.description: When worn, there is a 25% chance for a [[Slayer task]] kill to not count as a kill towards it, but still granting the appropriate Slayer experience (excluding [[TzTok-Jad]] and [[TzKal-Zuk]]). This results in Slayer tasks lasting 33.3% longer on average. This effect is the inverse of the [[expeditious bracelet]]s effect. Note that the bracelet needs to be worn '''only''' for the [[tick]] the [[Slayer]] XP drop appears for the effect to occur. This means that for the rest of the fight, other bracelets or gloves can be worn such as the [[Barrows gloves]]. The effects of the bracelet make it an ideal switch choice when completing desirable tasks, primarily [[boss]]es.

Digsite pendant.name: Digsite pendant
Digsite pendant.description: Unlike most gold [[jewellery]], this necklace cannot be enchanted until the spell has been learnt from one of the archaeologists cleaning finds in the [[Varrock Museum|museum]]. To learn how to enchant a ruby necklace, a player must first participate in cleaning [[uncleaned find]]s until a [[clean necklace]] is found in the sample; the chance of this is 1/51. If given to any of the archaeologists in the museum's cleaning area, the archaeologist will teach the player how to replicate the enchantment spell. This requires either 49 [[Magic]] or an [[enchant ruby or topaz]] tablet.

Asyn remains.name: Asyn remains
Asyn remains.description: To burn the asyn remains, the player needs [[yew pyre logs]] or better, level 65 Firemaking, and a [[tinderbox]]. First place the pyre logs on a [[Funeral Pyre|funeral pyre]], followed by the asyn remains, then light the pyre. This will grant the player [[Firemaking]] and [[Prayer]] experience (see table). Once burned, a black or silver [[shade key]], or some [[coins]], will appear next to the pyre. The keys can be used to either enter the catacombs or open the corresponding coloured doors to chests containing valuable items.

Phoenix necklace.name: Phoenix necklace
Phoenix necklace.description: In addition to restoring health, the phoenix necklace also clears out any pending attacks on the player from the attack buffer. This negates any pending damage from delayed attacks such as spells and arrows from afar. This also notably works on certain multi-hit [[special attacks]], such as those from [[dragon claws]] and [[Dark bow|dark bows]], where if one of the multi-hits triggers the effect, it will cancel the damage from subsequent multi-hits. The phoenix necklace is often brought in [[Player killing|PvP]] as a gear switch to counter these special attacks finishers.

Regen bracelet.name: Regen bracelet
Regen bracelet.description: When worn, it doubles the player's natural [[Hitpoints]] regeneration amount, healing 2 Hitpoints per minute instead of the standard 1 Hitpoint per minute. The effect of the regen bracelet stacks with either the [[Rapid Heal]] [[prayer]] or with the [[Hitpoints cape]] (which do not stack with each other); using either of these in conjunction with a regen bracelet effectively quadruples the natural rate of Hitpoint regeneration, increasing it to 2 Hitpoints per 30 seconds. This is a very helpful perk during activities that deal low amounts of continuous damage, reducing the need to bank frequently and rely on outside sources of healing. Examples of activities where it is helpful are fighting weak but accurate [[Non-player character|NPCs]], subduing the [[Wintertodt]], fighting [[Zalcano]], doing [[Pyramid plunder]], or [[pickpocketing]] (though most players would prefer the added chance of double loot from wearing [[rogue gloves]] while pickpocketing).

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sk.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Skotizo Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Sk.description: The '''Skotizo Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Skotizo]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Player killing/Mechanics.name: Player killing/Mechanics
Player killing/Mechanics.description: Player killers will often skull therefore they often use cheap, easily replaceable gear in case they die. If using Protect Item, they may opt to bring a valuable or powerful item knowing that they can protect it on death. However, this is vulnerable to prayer-draining methods such as the [[ancient mace]]'s [[Special attacks|special attack]] and the [[smite]] prayer. Should the player's prayer points hit 0, all of their prayers will deactivate (including Protect Item).

Amulet of chemistry.name: Amulet of chemistry
Amulet of chemistry.description: Each amulet begins with five charges. While the amulet is equipped, there is a 5% chance that you will create a 4-dose potion rather than a 3-dose potion when brewing potions (but with no extra experience), which consumes one charge. Once all of the amulet's charges are used up, the amulet crumbles to dust. When the amulet crumbles to dust, the player will either continue making potions or stop depending on the choice selected in the Options menu of the amulet. Each amulet lasts for an average of 100 potions made.

Teak plank.name: Teak plank
Teak plank.description: Teak planks can also be dropped in noted form from [[Gangster]]s and [[Gang boss]]es during the [[Tackle organised crime]] activity in [[Great Kourend]].

Auto Retaliate.name: Auto Retaliate
Auto Retaliate.description: '''Auto Retaliate''' is a [[Combat]]  that allows the player to choose whether their character fights back when attacked. Players can turn it on or off by going to the [[Combat Options]] tab and clicking the icon that says ''"Auto Retaliate (On)/(Off)"''.

Tolerance.name: Tolerance
Tolerance.description: '''Tolerance''' is a game mechanic which determines monsters' [[aggressiveness]] towards the [[player]].

Banshee.name: Banshee
Banshee.description: Much like [[cave crawler]]s, banshees regenerate their health back quickly, gaining back 1 hitpoint every 5 ticks.

Successful hit.name: Successful hit
Successful hit.description: This can be better explained by considering the following:

Elemental obelisks.name: Elemental obelisks
Elemental obelisks.description: To charge an [[unpowered orb]] it must be taken to the obelisk of the respective element that the player wishes to have the orb charged to, as well as the required runes to charge the orb.

Combat level.name: Combat level
Combat level.description: Normally, [[aggressive]] non-player characters stop attacking you when you reach higher than double their combat level. There are exceptions, however - for example, almost any monsters, except for [[Rat|Rats]], in the [[Wilderness]] will be aggressive no matter what your combat level is.

Adamant heraldic helm (Zamorak).name: Adamant heraldic helm (Zamorak)
Adamant heraldic helm (Zamorak).description: Players need level 70 [[Prayer]] in order to create the helm. Players can use a stand or easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Teleport to house (tablet).name: Teleport to house (tablet)
Teleport to house (tablet).description: Players can create this item on a [[mahogany eagle lectern]] (requiring 67 [[Construction]]) or [[marble lectern]] (77) as long as they have 1 [[law rune]], 1 [[air rune]], 1 [[earth rune]], and 1 [[soft clay]] and at least level 40 [[Magic]]. [[Combination runes]] and [[elemental staves|staves]] ''can'' be used, allowing for two spaces to be freed by using a [[dust staff]]. You gain 30 Magic [[experience]] for each tablet you create, and each tablet takes ~3 seconds to make.

Steel heraldic helm (Guthix).name: Steel heraldic helm (Guthix)
Steel heraldic helm (Guthix).description: Players need level 70 [[Prayer]] in order to create the helm. Players can use a stand or easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Obelisk of Earth.name: Obelisk of Earth
Obelisk of Earth.description: When using this obelisk it is recommended to have a method of curing [[poison]] in your bank as the [[poison spider]]s can poison you even if you have [[Protect from Melee]] prayer on. If you are low combat level and afraid that the poison may kill you, you can bring a method of curing poison with you at the price of having fewer orbs in your inventory. Alternatively, an [[Antipoison]] potion that grants immunity can be sipped at the bank right before you head to the obelisk as well. For instance, an [[Antidote++]] dose will grant 12 minutes of immunity, which is roughly 3-4 trips.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Kr.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Kree'arra Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Kr.description: The '''Kree'arra Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Kree'arra]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Non-degradable.name: Non-degradable
Non-degradable.description: '''Non-degradable''' [[armour]] and [[weapons]] are items that have an unlimited number of uses without becoming broken or destroyed.

Hard leather.name: Hard leather
Hard leather.description: Hard leather can also be obtained as rare loot from [[baby impling]]s.

Magic damage.name: Magic damage
Magic damage.description: Temporarily [[Boosting magic|boosting]] Magic increases magical attack accuracy, making it more likely to successfully hit a target. Except for [[Magic Dart]], increasing the Magic level does not increase the damage of [[spellbook]] [[combat spells]]. It does, however, increase damage for Magic Dart, [[salamanders]], [[Powered staff|powered staves]] (such as [[trident of the seas]]/[[trident of the swamp|swamp]], [[Thammaron's sceptre|Thammaron's]]/[[Accursed sceptre]], [[Sanguinesti staff]], and [[Tumeken's shadow|Tumeken's Shadow]]), and Magic [[special attacks]].

Prayer.name: Prayer
Prayer.description: [[Remains#Bones|Bones]] can be buried, offered to [[gilded altar]]s with [[incense burner]]s, offered to the altar in the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|Chaos Temple]], converted into [[Ectofuntus]], converted to [[Blessed bone shards]] and offered at the [[Libation bowl]], or have [[Sinister Offering]] cast on them. [[Remains#Demonic ashes|Demonic ashes]] can be scattered or converted into experience with [[Demonic Offering]]. Players can also kill [[monsters]] that were reanimated with [[reanimation spells]], or [[Shades of Mort'ton (minigame)|cremate shade remains]] to unlock chests. These chests can drop pieces of the [[zealot's robes]], a [[skilling outfit]] which gives a 1.25% chance per piece to save most [[remains]] when used.

Reanimated abyssal.name: Reanimated abyssal
Reanimated abyssal.description: Level 85 [[Slayer]] is required to inflict damage to this monster. Unlike regular [[Abyssal demon|abyssal demons]], they cannot teleport themselves or the player around.

Spiritual mage.name: Spiritual mage
Spiritual mage.description: Slaying a Spiritual mage in the God Wars Dungeon is a requirement for the [[Elite Fremennik Diary]] and slaying a Spiritual mage in the Wilderness God Wars Dungeon is a requirement for the [[Elite Wilderness Diary]].

Reanimated dog.name: Reanimated dog
Reanimated dog.description: They count towards [[dog]] [[Slayer task]]s, giving 35 [[Slayer]] experience per kill.

Abyssal bracelet.name: Abyssal bracelet
Abyssal bracelet.description: Wearing the bracelet will prevent the player from being [[Skull (status)|skulled]] when entering the [[Abyss]]. Each bracelet holds 5 charges, and 1 charge is used each time the wearer enters the Abyss. When all charges are used, the bracelet crumbles to dust.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Theatre of Blood Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.description: The '''Theatre of Blood Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Theatre of Blood]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Burnt jogre bones.name: Burnt jogre bones
Burnt jogre bones.description: Burnt jogre bones cannot be created by using jogre bones on a [[fire]]. Rather than becoming burnt, using jogre bones or burnt jogre bones on a fire prints the message {{mes|You heat the bones over the fire, but they don't look any different.}}

Amulet of glory.name: Amulet of glory
Amulet of glory.description: It is a very popular amulet in [[members]]-only worlds amongst players of all levels, as it provides good damage bonuses, has no requirements to wear, is much less expensive than the [[amulet of fury]], and offers useful [[teleport]]s.

Bandos altar.name: Bandos altar
Bandos altar.description: The '''Bandos altar''' is one of the five [[altar]]s found in the [[God Wars Dungeon]]. The altar can be used while fighting [[General Graardor]], as long as the player is not currently in combat. It can also be used to teleport out of the room at any time.

Dark Ankou.name: Dark Ankou
Dark Ankou.description: Whenever one of the four [[Awakened Altar|awakened altars]] is active, a timer of a random duration is set, which will spawn a dark ankou once it has ticked down.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1471467629827301378|date=16 December 2021|archiveurl=https://archive.is/XUr51|archivedate=24 June 2023|quote=[Do you know how the dark ankou at Skotizo works? (...)] Looks like it's off a timer on an open altar, with a random duration on that timer. So "it's random" might actually be the most appropriate answer.}}

Pyre logs.name: Pyre logs
Pyre logs.description: The amount of experience shown in the table below is the experience that is rewarded for using the required amount of oil on a log. However, the actual experience per log is calculated based on the amount of oil in the vial that is being used. For example, using [[sacred oil(4)]] on an [[oak log]] will result in two doses of oil being used up, and 16 experience being rewarded. Using the remaining two doses of oil will then reward 10 more experience, since a vial containing 2 doses is being used. Because of this, when using full vials of oil, one can expect higher average amounts of experience per log than shown in this table. Making pyre logs does benefit from the pyromancer outfit's experience boosting properties unlike other firemaking activities used in the Shades of Mort'ton minigame.

Chaos altar (Prayer).name: Chaos altar (Prayer)
Chaos altar (Prayer).description: Praying at the chaos altar in the [[Yanille Agility dungeon]] opens a trapdoor, damaging the player and dropping them to the lower level of the dungeon where [[poison spider]]s reside.

Snailfeet's bone.name: Snailfeet's bone
Snailfeet's bone.description: The bone is to be buried in [[Yu'biusk]], in which Snailfeet's soul will be freed and 2,500 [[Prayer]] experience is given. The experience is not affected by [[chewed bones]]' effect. If players attempt to bury it anywhere else but Yu'biusk, a message in the chatbox will state {{mes|You should go to Yu'biusk before you bury this bone.}}

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Da.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Dagannoth Kings Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Da.description: The '''Dagannoth Kings Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Dagannoth Kings]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Ecumenical key.name: Ecumenical key
Ecumenical key.description: The keys are only recommended for trips at [[Kree'arra]] or [[Commander Zilyana]], as their soldiers take longer to kill. They are not recommended for [[General Graardor]], [[K'ril Tsutsaroth]], and [[Nex]], due to the former two having weak soldiers that can be quickly killed, and the latter's counting for multiple essence per kill.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Kr.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Kraken Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Kr.description: The '''Kraken Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Kraken]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 22 June 2021, at an index of 100.

Big chest.name: Big chest
Big chest.description: During the quest, players can 'Inspect' the chest to learn about the chest from [[Kovac]].

Tormented bracelet.name: Tormented bracelet
Tormented bracelet.description: Wearing any piece of enchanted [[zenyte]] equipment requires level 75 in [[Hitpoints]].

Calculator:Enchantment.name: Calculator:Enchantment
Calculator:Enchantment.description: This will automatically deduct the current price of [[Cosmic rune]]s, other runes and materials from profit. The calculator assumes you are using the correct [[elemental staves|staff]] for unlimited elemental [[runes]].

Reanimated hellhound.name: Reanimated hellhound
Reanimated hellhound.description: Killing a reanimated hellhound will count towards a [[Hellhound]] [[slayer task]].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/The Nightmare Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.description: The '''The Nightmare Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[The Nightmare]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Exchange:Trailblazer reloaded relic hunt.name: Exchange:Trailblazer reloaded relic hunter (t2) armour set

Altar of nature.name: Altar of nature
Altar of nature.description: The '''Altar of nature''' in the [[Nature Grotto]] is repaired during the [[Nature Spirit]] [[quest]]. Praying at the altar restores [[prayer]] points, and gives 2 extra points.

Saturated heart.name: Saturated heart
Saturated heart.description: The heart grants a 5-minute temporary boost that increases the player's [[Magic]] level by 4 + 10% of their level, rounded down (compared to the imbued heart's 1 + 10% boost). In addition, the player's Magic level will not drain below the maximum boost of the heart when used, though it can still be decreased by the use of certain potions or by attacks from an opponent. After five minutes, the player's Magic level will return to normal.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ve.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Venenatis Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ve.description: The '''Venenatis Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Venenatis]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Ensouled minotaur head.name: Ensouled minotaur head
Ensouled minotaur head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Bank Deposit Box.name: Bank Deposit Box
Bank Deposit Box.description: A '''bank deposit box''' allows players to deposit items directly into the [[bank]] from their inventory without having to open the bank interface. Unlike [[banker]]s, [[bank booth]]s, or [[bank chest]]s, deposit boxes are one-click and do not require entering a [[bank PIN]], allowing for faster depositing times when [[skill]]ing, [[Resources|resource]] gathering, or [[World switching|world hopping]]; however, they cannot be used to withdraw items or check the contents of a player's bank account. Bank deposit boxes can be found in most bank buildings and in a few other areas.

Prayer items.name: Prayer items
Prayer items.description: For example, having +30 Prayer bonus would make Prayers last 100% longer (twice as long). [[Protect from Melee]] would then drain 1 Prayer point every 6 seconds, instead of every 3 seconds. The highest Prayer bonus possible is 73.

Sawmill voucher.name: Sawmill voucher
Sawmill voucher.description: Sawmill vouchers cannot be used by [[Butler|butlers]] when asking them to convert logs into planks.

Amulet of magic.name: Amulet of magic
Amulet of magic.description: A normal amulet of magic, as well as its [[Amulet of magic (t)|trimmed variant]] are both possible reward for the completion of easy [[Treasure Trails]].

Exchange:Raging echoes relic hunter (t1).name: Exchange:Raging echoes relic hunter (t1) armour set

Lumbridge teleport (tablet).name: Lumbridge teleport (tablet)
Lumbridge teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on either an [[Eagle lectern]], [[Teak eagle lectern]], or [[Mahogany eagle lectern]] as long as they have 1 [[law rune]], 3 [[air rune]]s, 1 [[earth rune]], and 1 [[soft clay]] and at least level 31 [[Magic]].

Salve graveyard teleport (tablet).name: Salve graveyard teleport (tablet)
Salve graveyard teleport (tablet).description: If the player has not completed the [[Priest in Peril]] quest and spoke to [[Drezel]] before entering [[Morytania]], they will receive a message in the chatbox stating ''You must have completed Priest in Peril and received Drezel's warning to cast this spell.''

Sulphur Nagua.name: Sulphur Nagua
Sulphur Nagua.description: Their attacks are unique in that they hit twice per attack, rolling damage normally and splitting it in two [[hitsplats]]. After five attacks they will use a special attack in which they raise their weapon, and if the player remains within their melee range (including diagonal spaces) after three ticks, they will have 5 [[prayer points]] drained.

Ahrim the Blighted.name: Ahrim the Blighted
Ahrim the Blighted.description: It is recommended that the player uses [[Protect from Magic]] when fighting him due to his accuracy - although note that it will '''not''' protect against his stat reductions. Even if using the Protect from Magic prayer, his stat reduction spells can still work, plus his set effect can still activate because the attack still counts as a successful hit, so the use of dragonhide armour and bringing a [[Stat restore potion]] is recommended.

Enraged barbarian spirit.name: Enraged barbarian spirit
Enraged barbarian spirit.description: These are a common option for an [[Ironman mode|ironman account]] to get a [[mith grapple]] or [[yew shortbow]].

Temporary skill boost.name: Temporary skill boost
Temporary skill boost.description: There are several restrictions to these temporary boosts. Note that they do not work on certain quest and diary requirements, and do not work on minigame requirements at all. Temporary skill boosts do not allow the player to equip items that require a level higher than their current base level. However, skill decreases below a certain level do not prevent the player from equipping items they normally can equip at base level (e.g. if a player with 60 Attack drinks [[beer]] to lower their level below 60, they can still wield [[dragon weapons]]).

Games necklace.name: Games necklace
Games necklace.description: When a games necklace has one charge remaining, it is recommended not to use the last charge, but instead to save it and cast [[High Level Alchemy]] on it, as the necklace's alchemy value is irrespective of its charge.

Ensouled troll head.name: Ensouled troll head
Ensouled troll head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Amulet of power.name: Amulet of power
Amulet of power.description: This item is a less expensive option for players who do not wish to buy an [[amulet of glory]]. It lacks the glory's teleportation capabilities and has weaker [[Attack bonus|attack]] and [[Prayer bonus]]es, but has the same [[Strength bonus|strength]] bonus as well as higher [[defence bonus]]es.

Ghorrock teleport (tablet).name: Ghorrock teleport (tablet)
Ghorrock teleport (tablet).description: Because this tablet teleports players to the Wilderness, a warning will appear upon clicking the "Break" option on the tablet. This can be toggled by right-clicking the "Configure" option.

Revenant hobgoblin.name: Revenant hobgoblin
Revenant hobgoblin.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/FA.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/FAQ
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/FA.description: The [[Grand Exchange Market Watch]] is a project set up to monitor and record the prices and other information on items on the [[Grand Exchange]].

Exchange:Trailblazer reloaded relic hunt.name: Exchange:Trailblazer reloaded relic hunter (t1) armour set

Mosschin's bone.name: Mosschin's bone
Mosschin's bone.description: The bone is to be buried in [[Yu'biusk]], in which Mosschin's soul will be freed and 5,000 [[Prayer]] experience is given. The experience is not affected by [[chewed bones]]' effect. If players attempt to bury it anywhere else but Yu'biusk, a message in the chatbox will state {{mes|You should go to Yu'biusk before you bury this bone.}}

Long bone.name: Long bone
Long bone.description: After completion of [[Death to the Dorgeshuun]], long bones may be sold to [[Barlak]], in [[Dorgesh-Kaan]], for {{NoCoins|1000}} coins each. Note that Barlak can take them from your bank, so it is not necessary to have any bones in your inventory. At level 30 [[Construction]], he will give a lecture about the skill granting 4,500 Construction [[experience]] per bone, equivalent to {{NoCoins|floor(4500/60*{{GEP|Oak plank}})}} coins worth of [[oak plank]]s. He will convert all long bones in the player's inventory and bank at once. The [[Carpenter's outfit|Carpenter's Outfit]] will not apply to the Construction experience rewarded. This level 30 Construction requirement is not boostable.

Enchant sapphire or opal.name: Enchant sapphire or opal
Enchant sapphire or opal.description: As with all magic tablets, using this tablet does not have a Magic level requirement and grants no experience.

Ensouled head.name: Ensouled head
Ensouled head.description: When reanimated, the monster will attack after the animation completes, and they will override [[Single-way combat]] rules. The monster has 35 hitpoints, and upon killing it will reward [[Prayer]] experience. The amount of Prayer experience gained increases with higher-levelled heads. Reanimation spells are divided into four tiers, which determines the [[Magic]] level required in order to use the spell. Some reanimated monsters do have additional requirements, so players should take note of this before reanimating a head.

Fire orb.name: Fire orb
Fire orb.description: A fire orb can be used on a [[battlestaff]], requiring 62 [[Crafting]], yielding a [[fire battlestaff]] and 125 Crafting experience.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Gi.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Giant Mole Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Gi.description: The '''Giant Mole Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Giant Mole]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Paddewwa teleport (tablet).name: Paddewwa teleport (tablet)
Paddewwa teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Ancient)|ancient lectern]] by the altar inside the [[Ancient Pyramid]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 2 [[law rune]]s, 1 [[air rune]], and 1 [[fire rune]].  Level 54 [[Magic]] is required while being on the [[Ancient Magicks]] spellbook. Making the teleport tablet gives 64 Magic [[experience]].

Prayer points.name: Prayer points
Prayer points.description: The player's current prayer points are displayed on the game's [[skills tab]] and are displayed by the [[minimap]] if the Data orb option is toggled on. The number of prayer points the player has remaining is an indication of how long a player can use prayers before having to restore them. The player can left-click on the prayer orb to begin using [[quick prayers]], or the player can right-click on the prayer orb to set up their desired quick prayers.

Reanimated demon.name: Reanimated demon
Reanimated demon.description: Killing a Reanimated demon will count towards a lesser demon slayer task.

Ensouled horror head.name: Ensouled horror head
Ensouled horror head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Soft clay.name: Soft clay
Soft clay.description: The only place to mine soft clay directly is in the [[Trahaearn mine]], where [[soft clay rocks]] can be found. In addition, wearing a [[bracelet of clay]] in this mine can yield 2 soft clays per action, whereas mining clay rocks elsewhere yields only a single soft clay per action.

Elidinis Statuette.name: Elidinis Statuette
Elidinis Statuette.description: Prior to the events of the [[Spirits of the Elid]] [[quest]], the priestess' spot on the shrine had been vacant for the last five years. This lead some people to suspect that the goddess, in her anger, dried up Nardah's water supply. Currently, [[Shiratti the Custodian]] maintains the shrine. An [[ancestral key]] can be found on a table to the east of the building, which is used during the [[Spirits of the Elid]] [[quest]] along with a [[torn robe]] in the cupboard to the west of the building.

Rune heraldic helm (Guthix).name: Rune heraldic helm (Guthix)
Rune heraldic helm (Guthix).description: Players need level 70 [[Prayer]] in order to create the helm. Players can use a stand or easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Ensouled unicorn head.name: Ensouled unicorn head
Ensouled unicorn head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Lo.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Log Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Lo.description: The '''Log Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current logs listed in the [[Market Watch]], with the starting date of this average being on 13 June 2020, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of log prices is reflected in this index.

Enchant emerald or jade.name: Enchant emerald or jade
Enchant emerald or jade.description: This tablet can be made regardless of the player's current spell book. Using a [[Staff of air]] can reduce the cost of casting the spell.

User:Maimegidola/Sandbox.name: User:Maimegidola/Sandbox
User:Maimegidola/Sandbox.description: Players can also quickly deposit items into the deposit box simply by using the item directly on it. If the player has more than one of the item in their inventory, the player will be prompted to select or enter the number of items they want to deposit, otherwise the single item will be deposited immediately.

Nazastarool.name: Nazastarool
Nazastarool.description: Poison and venom will persist through phase changes after defeating a form. Recurrent damage in Nightmare Zone will also continue onto the next form.

Dareeyak teleport (tablet).name: Dareeyak teleport (tablet)
Dareeyak teleport (tablet).description: Because this tablet teleports players to the Wilderness, a warning will appear upon clicking the "Break" option on the tablet. This can be toggled by right-clicking the "Configure" option.

Grand Exchange/Non-tradeable items.name: Grand Exchange/Non-tradeable items
Grand Exchange/Non-tradeable items.description: '''Non-tradeable items''', in terms of the [[Grand Exchange]], are [[items]] that are [[tradeable]], but not on the Grand Exchange. These items must therefore be exchanged via the standard [[Trading#First trade window|trading interface]].

Ensouled demon head.name: Ensouled demon head
Ensouled demon head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Libation bowl.name: Libation bowl
Libation bowl.description: The player can check how many remaining charges the libation bowl has by right-clicking the "Check" option. As jugs of blessed wine '''cannot''' be banked, it is recommended that players only bring and bless as many wines at the [[exposed altar]] in proportion to the amount of shards they have.

Magic.name: Magic
Magic.description: Magic is also important in order to defend well against Magic attacks. Unlike [[Melee Defence|Melee]] and [[Defence#Mechanics|Ranged defence]], a player's [[Magic defence]] is actually determined by both Magic (70%) and [[Defence]] (30%) levels, as well as Magic defence bonus.

Ensouled abyssal head.name: Ensouled abyssal head
Ensouled abyssal head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Ensouled chaos druid head.name: Ensouled chaos druid head
Ensouled chaos druid head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Falador teleport (tablet).name: Falador teleport (tablet)
Falador teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on an [[eagle lectern]], a [[teak eagle lectern]], or a [[mahogany eagle lectern]]. To make it, level 37 [[Magic]], 1 [[law rune]], 3 [[air rune]]s, 1 [[water rune]], and 1 [[soft clay]] is required, which grants 48 experience. A single Falador tablet can be obtained from [[Marlo's crate]], a reward from the [[Daddy's Home]] miniquest.

Catfish.name: Catfish
Catfish.description: Catfish can be obtained by preparing a [[raw catfish]] on the [[preparation table]] whilst having a [[knife]]. Preparing catfish requires level 46 [[Cooking]] and grants 43 experience when successful. Players may ruin the catfish during preparation, resulting in a [[ruined catfish]]; the [[burn rate|chance of failure]] while preparing these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels.

Fishing guild teleport (tablet).name: Fishing guild teleport (tablet)
Fishing guild teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Lunar)|lunar lectern]] in the ceremonial building on [[Lunar Isle]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 3 [[law rune]]s, 10 [[water rune]]s, and 3 [[astral rune]]s, as well as level 85 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Lunar spellbook]].

Mage Training Arena.name: Mage Training Arena
Mage Training Arena.description: To participate in all the activities, one should bring [[nature rune]]s, [[cosmic runes]], [[law runes]], and all types of elemental runes (or staves to replace them). The spells cast are:

User:Jie/GE.name: User:Jie/GE
User:Jie/GE.description: The following is a list of all buying limits for items purchasable from the Grand Exchange:

Raurg bones.name: Raurg bones
Raurg bones.description: If burying the raurg bones in [[Jiggig]], there's a 1 in 3{{fact}} chance to give no Prayer experience, and to instead spawn a [[skogre]]. The skogre will despawn after 5 minutes. A message in the chatbox appears "The creature rises from the grave... again!".

Venator icon.name: Venator icon
Venator icon.description: The icon must be brought to a [[furnace]], alongside three [[chromium ingot]]s and a [[ring mould]], to craft the [[venator ring]]. The entire process requires level 90 [[Magic]] and 80 [[Crafting]], which can be boosted.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ar.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Araxxor Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ar.description: The '''Araxxor Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Araxxor]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 16 October 2024, at an index of 100.

Altar (Forthos Dungeon).name: Altar (Forthos Dungeon)
Altar (Forthos Dungeon).description: Players who attempt to kill [[Olbertus]] in the room will result in him transforming into a level-186 [[Shaeded Beast]], who will [[Cursed Altar|curse the Altar]] and render it unusable until a sufficient amount of eligible dragon bones are offered to the [[sacred bone burner]] in the Crypt of the Moon (see [[Sacred Bone Burner#Faith level|here for more info]]). Attempting to use the altar while it is still cursed will result in the player taking up to 30 damage and fully depleting their prayer.

Soulreaper axe.name: Soulreaper axe
Soulreaper axe.description: The axe has a passive on-attack effect, which damages the wielder 8 Hitpoints, and grants a "''Soul stack''" for every attack they make. As long as a player is not at the maximum amount of stacks (5) and has more than 8 hitpoints, they will take damage and receive one stack of this effect. Each ''Soul stack'' provides a 6% boost to a player's [[Strength]] Level, up to a maximum of +30% at five stacks. These stacks can be used for the Special Attack ''Behead'', or lost at the rate of one per 20 ticks (12 seconds) of the player not attacking. The player is healed for 8 hitpoints for each ''Soul stack'' lost over time or otherwise used through the special attack.

Ensouled bear head.name: Ensouled bear head
Ensouled bear head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Necromancy.name: Necromancy
Necromancy.description: The animation of [[undead]] such as [[skeleton]]s and [[zombie]]s are the usual fare for necromancers, and have often been used as disposable troops, as seen during the [[God Wars]]. Although on the surface appearing similar to Summoning, necromancy and summoning have nothing to do with each other{{CiteNPC|npc=Malignius Mortifer|quote=The obscure magical art of necromancy has nothing to do with Summoning.}}. Necromancers are apparently capable of bringing themselves back from the dead.

Jug of blessed wine.name: Jug of blessed wine
Jug of blessed wine.description: Alternatively, players may use a [[jug of blessed sunfire wine]] instead, which gives each bone shard 6 [[Prayer]] experience instead of 5. This requires having added two [[sunfire splinters]] to an unblessed [[jug of wine]]; sunfire splinters '''cannot''' be added to a jug of blessed wine.

Ancient wyvern shield.name: Ancient wyvern shield
Ancient wyvern shield.description: The shield provides both [[dragonfire]] protection and greater protection against the icy breath of [[wyverns]]. Unlike the [[Elemental shield|elemental]], [[Mind shield|mind]], and [[dragonfire shield]]s, the ancient wyvern shield will also grant an immunity against the freezing effect from a wyvern's [[icy breath]], as well as reducing the damage. This immunity, on the other hand, '''does not''' extend to any other [[Stun (status)|freezing effect]] (such as [[KBD]], [[Vorkath]], etc).

Ensouled giant head.name: Ensouled giant head
Ensouled giant head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Civitas illa fortis teleport (tablet).name: Civitas illa fortis teleport (tablet)
Civitas illa fortis teleport (tablet).description: Players with level 54 [[Magic]] can create this item on a [[Mahogany eagle lectern]] or better in a [[player-owned house]]. This requires 2 [[law rune]]s, 1 [[fire rune]], 1 [[earth rune]], and 1 [[soft clay]]. Creating a tablet grants 64 Magic experience, the same as casting the Civitas illa Fortis Teleport spell. [[Elemental staves]] can be substituted for [[runes]] and are recommended when making teleport tablets in large groups at a time.

Steel heraldic helm (Saradomin).name: Steel heraldic helm (Saradomin)
Steel heraldic helm (Saradomin).description: Players need level 70 [[Prayer]] in order to create the helm. Players can use a stand or easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Bank chest.name: Bank chest
Bank chest.description: A '''bank chest''' is an interactive scenery item that allows quick access to a player's [[bank]] account, usually found in remote locations or places where a normal bank would not fit. Like any other banking facility it is indicated with a bank icon ([[File:Bank icon.png|($)]]).

Draynor manor teleport (tablet).name: Draynor manor teleport (tablet)
Draynor manor teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Arceuus)|Arceuus lectern]] in the [[Ouditor]]'s house with 1 [[law rune]], 1 [[earth rune]], 1 [[water rune]], and level 17 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Arceuus spellbook]]. In addition, a [[dark essence block]] is required to substitute [[soft clay]].

Phrin Shade.name: Phrin Shade
Phrin Shade.description: As with all [[Shades (Shades of Mort'ton)|shades in Mort'ton]], Phrin shades possess 2 traits you should be aware of:

Gorilla bones.name: Gorilla bones
Gorilla bones.description: [[Zooknock]] is able to make a [[gorilla greegree]] with the bones in the Ape Atoll Dungeon. If players want to make a [[bearded gorilla greegree]], they must use [[bearded gorilla bones]] instead. After completion of [[Monkey Madness II]], players no longer need to bring bones; they can simply claim the greegree from [[Zooknock]] in the [[Tree Gnome Stronghold]].

Unholy symbol.name: Unholy symbol
Unholy symbol.description: Finally, the symbol must be blessed either by the [[Spirit of Scorpius]] at the [[Scorpius Shrine]], north of the [[Observatory]], or by using an [[Unholy book]] or [[Book of balance]] with it. To bless the symbol using one of the books, a player must have a [[Prayer]] level of 50 or higher, and blessing the symbol makes the player expend <math>(\frac{1}{10} * CurrentPrayerPoints) + 2</math> amount of [[Prayer]] points. Once blessed, the unpowered symbol becomes an unholy symbol and gains stat bonuses.

Dragon bones.name: Dragon bones
Dragon bones.description: The relative ease of collecting dragon bones, combined with the amount of experience earned from them, makes them widely viewed as a fast, cost-effective way to train Prayer.

Abyssal head.name: Abyssal head
Abyssal head.description: It can be combined with a [[Slayer helmet]] or [[Slayer helmet (i)]] to create a [[red slayer helmet|red Slayer helmet]] or [[red slayer helmet (i)|red Slayer helmet (i)]], respectively. Doing so requires purchasing the ability ''Unholy Helmet'' for 1,000 [[Slayer reward point]]s.

Senntisten teleport (tablet).name: Senntisten teleport (tablet)
Senntisten teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Ancient)|ancient lectern]] by the altar inside the [[Ancient Pyramid]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 2 [[law rune]]s, and 1 [[soul rune]], as well as level 60 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Ancient Magicks]] spellbook.

Adamant kiteshield (Zamorak).name: Adamant kiteshield (Zamorak)
Adamant kiteshield (Zamorak).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to make the kiteshield. Players can use an easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Barrows teleport (tablet).name: Barrows teleport (tablet)
Barrows teleport (tablet).description: Players with 83 [[Magic]] and the [[Arceuus spellbook]] active can create this item on the [[Lectern (Arceuus)|Arceuus lectern]] in the [[Ouditor]]'s house with 2 [[law rune]]s, 2 [[soul rune]]s, 1 [[blood rune]], and a [[dark essence block]] (instead of the [[soft clay]] required for [[standard spellbook]] magic tablets). Making this tablet grants 90 Magic [[experience]], the same as if casting the spell.

Rune heraldic helm (Zamorak).name: Rune heraldic helm (Zamorak)
Rune heraldic helm (Zamorak).description: Players need level 70 [[Prayer]] in order to create the helm. Players can use a stand or easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Kurask head.name: Kurask head
Kurask head.description: Before it can be [[Kurask head (mounted)|mounted]] in a [[Skill Hall]] within a [[player-owned house]], it must be stuffed by the [[Taxidermist]] in [[Canifis]], where she will charge 6,000 coins and return a [[stuffed kurask head]] to the player. They can then mount the head using 2 [[mahogany plank]]s which requires 58 [[construction]]. When players take it to the Taxidermist, she will tell the player ''"A kurask? Splendid! Look at those horns!"''

Enchant dragonstone.name: Enchant dragonstone
Enchant dragonstone.description: This tablet can be made regardless of the player's current [[spellbook]]. Using a [[Mud battlestaff]] can greatly reduce the cost of casting the spell.

Bones to bananas (tablet).name: Bones to bananas (tablet)
Bones to bananas (tablet).description: Players can create this item on either a [[Demon lectern|demon]], [[Teak demon lectern|teak demon]], [[mahogany demon lectern| mahogany demon]] or [[marble lectern]] as long as they have 1 [[nature rune]], 2 [[earth rune]]s, 2 [[water rune]]s, and 1 [[soft clay]] and at least level 15 [[Magic]]. Using a [[mud battlestaff]], [[staff of earth]], or [[staff of water]] can make this more cost-effective. The spell is transferred to a piece of soft clay at a lectern in the [[Study]] of a [[player-owned house]], creating a magic tablet. The [[experience]] for casting the spell is gained at the time the tablet is created.

Kourend castle teleport (tablet).name: Kourend castle teleport (tablet)
Kourend castle teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on a [[Teak eagle lectern]], a [[Mahogany eagle lectern]], or a [[Marble lectern|Marble Lectern]] with 2 [[law rune]]s, 1 [[water rune]], 1 [[fire rune]], and 1 [[soft clay]] and at least level 48 [[Magic]], granting 58 experience.

Ring of recoil.name: Ring of recoil
Ring of recoil.description: To see the remaining damage the ring can deal, the player can check it, while equipped, in the [[Worn Equipment]] interface. The amount of damage left is kept track of for each player, not each ring; thus, a newly-equipped ring will have the same number of charges remaining as any other ring the player wears. If the player wishes to obtain a ring with 40 charges remaining, the player must use any ring of recoil completely until it shatters, or use the right-click "Break" option on a ring while in the [[inventory]].

Crawling hand (item).name: Crawling hand (item)
Crawling hand (item).description: Before it can be [[Crawling hand (mounted)|mounted]] in a [[Skill Hall]] within a [[player-owned house]], it must be stuffed by the [[Taxidermist]] in [[Canifis]], where she will charge 1,000 coins and return a [[stuffed crawling hand]] to the player. They can then mount the hand using 2 [[teak plank]]s. When players take it to the Taxidermist, she will tell the player ''"That's a very fine crawling hand."''

Spiritual warrior.name: Spiritual warrior
Spiritual warrior.description: Spiritual warriors frequently drop [[mithril equipment]], [[adamant equipment]] and [[rune equipment]], so it is advisable to bring runes for [[High Level Alchemy]].

Amulet of strength.name: Amulet of strength
Amulet of strength.description: A [[strength amulet (t)|trimmed]] version of the amulet of strength is available from [[medium clue scroll]]s.

Alchemical hydra heads.name: Alchemical hydra heads
Alchemical hydra heads.description: It can also be [[Alchemical hydra heads (mounted)|mounted]] in a [[Skill Hall]] in a [[player-owned house]]. Before it can be mounted, it must be stuffed by the [[Taxidermist]] in [[Canifis]], where she will charge 50,000 coins and return [[stuffed hydra heads]] to the player. They can then mount the heads using 2 [[mahogany plank]]s and 2 gold leaves. When players take it to the Taxidermist, she will exclaim ''"This hydra looks like it might fall to pieces soon. I'll have to be careful to preserve it properly."''

Melee.name: Melee
Melee.description: Players can also use Melee [[prayer]]s such as [[Piety]] to improve Melee combat.

Maximum melee hit.name: Maximum melee hit
Maximum melee hit.description: The max possible hit through normal gameplay means is 195. This is accomplished at 99 Strength by utilising the best Strength equipment, the [[Piety]] prayer, the [[Dragon battleaxe]] special attack, a [[Black mask]], and the [[Keris partisan]] on a [[Kalphite (attribute)|Kalphite]] while on the appropriate slayer task for the monster. The only kalphites with enough hit points to reach this hit are the [[Kalphite Queen]], the [[Giant Scarab]], and [[Kephri]], given a high enough [[invocation]]. In this scenario, the chance of hitting 195 is 1 in 3315, assuming a successful hit. An even higher max hit is possible while in the [[Tombs of Amascut]], due to additional item options which can only be used within the raid. For free-to-play the maximum hit is 31, using a [[Rune 2h sword]], an [[Amulet of strength]], [[Decorative boots (gold)]] and a [[Strength potion]] with [[Ultimate Strength]] active.

Ensouled bloodveld head.name: Ensouled bloodveld head
Ensouled bloodveld head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Skills necklace.name: Skills necklace
Skills necklace.description: A skills necklace can be recharged at the [[Totem Pole (Legends' Guild)|totem pole]] in the [[Legends' Guild]], at the [[Fountain of Uhld]] in the [[Myths' Guild]], or by casting [[Recharge Dragonstone]], giving it four charges. Players who have completed [[Legends' Quest]] can also recharge it at the [[Fountain of Rune]], giving it six charges.

Harmony island teleport (tablet).name: Harmony island teleport (tablet)
Harmony island teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Arceuus)|Arceuus lectern]] in the [[Ouditor]]'s house with 1 [[law rune]], 1 [[soul rune]], 1 [[nature rune]], and level 65 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Arceuus spellbook]]. A [[dark essence block]] is also required. Making the teleport tablet grants 74 Magic [[experience]].

Mind altar teleport (tablet).name: Mind altar teleport (tablet)
Mind altar teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Arceuus)|Arceuus lectern]] in the [[Ouditor]]'s house with 1 [[law rune]], 2 [[mind rune]]s, and level 28 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Arceuus spellbook]]. In addition, a [[dark essence block]] is required to substitute [[soft clay]].

Ring of returning.name: Ring of returning
Ring of returning.description: The ring will provide five charges before degrading to dust.

Evil spirit.name: Evil spirit
Evil spirit.description: The player can use numerous crates, barrels or even brewers as safespots. It's also possible to make the evil spirit lose its aggro by running on the eastern walkway outside the brewery or using ladders or stairs to move on different floors.

Ensouled hellhound head.name: Ensouled hellhound head
Ensouled hellhound head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Saradomin Brazier.name: Saradomin Brazier
Saradomin Brazier.description: If equipped, the [[hallowed symbol]] will reduce the amount of [[vampyre dust]] needed from two to one. This does not reduce the awarded experience.

Revenant dragon.name: Revenant dragon
Revenant dragon.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

Asyn Shade.name: Asyn Shade
Asyn Shade.description: As with all [[Shades (Shades of Mort'ton)|shades in Mort'ton]], Asyn shades possess 2 traits you should be aware of:

Large zombie monkey bones.name: Large zombie monkey bones
Large zombie monkey bones.description: [[Zooknock]] is able to make a [[Zombie monkey greegree (big)|big zombie monkey greegree]] with the bones in the Ape Atoll Dungeon. If players want to make a [[Zombie monkey greegree (small)|small zombie monkey greegree]], they must use [[small zombie monkey bones]] instead. After completion of [[Monkey Madness II]], players no longer need to bring bones; they can simply claim the greegree from [[Zooknock]] in the [[Tree Gnome Stronghold]].

Eternal boots.name: Eternal boots
