Eternal boots.description: They can be created by using an [[eternal crystal]] with a pair of [[infinity boots]]. This process cannot be reversed, and requires level 60 in [[Runecraft]] and [[Magic]] (boosts cannot be used), granting 200 experience in both skills.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/The Leviathan Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.description: The '''The Leviathan Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[The Leviathan]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 13 October 2024, at an index of 100.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Go.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/God Wars Dungeon

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/The Hueycoatl Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.description: The '''The Hueycoatl Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[The Hueycoatl ]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 16 October 2024, at an index of 100.

Death wing.name: Death wing
Death wing.description: '''Death wings''' are flying monsters that appear in the [[Legends' Quest]]. The death wings are located in a remote area, and have no drops, so very few players train on them. Killing a death wing is one of the hard tasks in the [[Karamja Diary]].

Ultor ring.name: Ultor ring
Ultor ring.description: The ring requires level 90 [[Magic]] and 80 [[Crafting]] to create (both being boostable), as well as having learnt how to combine Fremennik ring icons with ancient vestiges via [[Peer the Seer]].

Revenant pyrefiend.name: Revenant pyrefiend
Revenant pyrefiend.description: The [[Salve amulet]] can be a good option for killing revenants due to the damage bonus it provides while being easily replaceable, as [[PKing]] in the Revenant Caves is extremely common.

Maple pyre logs.name: Maple pyre logs
Maple pyre logs.description: To create the oil, players need to purchase normal [[olive oil]] from [[Razmire Keelgan]]'s store in [[Mort'ton]] and then help to restore the temple that lies to the north of the town. Once the temple is rebuilt, players may light the altar in the centre of the temple and use their olive oil on the fire. This converts the ordinary [[olive oil]] into sacred oil, spending some sanctity percentage.

Mithril bar.name: Mithril bar
Mithril bar.description: A mithril bar can be smithed on an [[anvil]] by using the Smithing skill to create [[mithril weapons]] and [[mithril armour|armour]], granting 50 Smithing experience per bar used. A list of mithril items that can be smithed from mithril bars and the Smithing levels required can be found at Smithing tables.

Armadyl altar.name: Armadyl altar
Armadyl altar.description: Praying at the altar will fully restore your [[prayer]] and give a +1 prayer bonus for every piece of equipment affiliated to [[Armadyl]]. After praying at the altar, you cannot pray at it again for 10 minutes; players can attempt to pray at the altar to see how much time they have left.

Teak pyre logs.name: Teak pyre logs
Teak pyre logs.description: Once the sacred oil has been obtained players will need to use three doses of it upon some [[teak logs]]. These logs will then become teak pyre logs and grants 14 Firemaking experience.

Drops.name: Drops
Drops.description: Large monsters (that take up more than one square) will always drop their drops in the south-westernmost square. This also applies to any [[Ranged]] [[ammunition]] that falls to the ground when ranging those monsters.

Attack.name: Attack
Attack.description: See also [[Armour/Highest bonuses|the highest possible bonuses for each style]].

Altar (Lovakengj).name: Altar (Lovakengj)
Altar (Lovakengj).description: An '''altar''' can be found in [[Lovakengj]]. Like most [[altar]]s, players can recharge their [[prayer]] points at this altar. It resembles a [[Runic Altar (The Forsaken Tower)|similar altar]] in [[The Forsaken Tower (location)|the Forsaken Tower]].

Banner (Saradomin).name: Banner (Saradomin)
Banner (Saradomin).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to make the Saradomin banner. Sir Renitee will not assign a crest unless the player has over level 16 [[Construction]]. Players can use a Banner easel in another player's house if they do not have one.

Bird's egg.name: Bird's egg
Bird's egg.description: These eggs can be offered to the [[shrine]] in the [[Woodcutting Guild]] to receive 100 [[Prayer]] [[experience]] and a [[bird nest]] with seeds or a piece of the [[evil chicken outfit]] as a reward. Each piece of the evil chicken outfit has a 1/1200 chance of being awarded, resulting in approximately a 1/300 chance of receiving any outfit piece.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1259915895343890434|date=11 May 2020|archiveurl=http://archive.md/Rs2eU|archivedate=24 Aug 2020|quote=The head is 1/1200. The wings are 1/1200. The legs are 1/1200. The feet are 1/1200. Thus the chance of getting an outfit piece is 1/300.}} Any outfit piece will replace a nest, so a full inventory will not compromise receiving the outfit piece.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Thermonuclear smoke devil Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.description: The '''Thermonuclear smoke devil Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Thermonuclear smoke devil]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 22 June 2021, at an index of 100.

Kalphite Queen head (mounted).name: Kalphite Queen head (mounted)
Kalphite Queen head (mounted).description: Players must complete [[Priest in Peril]] to be able to [[Taxidermist|stuff]] the [[kq head]] or [[kq head (tattered)]]. If players remove the mounted head, they will receive nothing back.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Mo.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Moons of Peril Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Mo.description: The '''The Moons of Peril Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[The Moons of Peril]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 16 October 2024, at an index of 100.

Loar Shade.name: Loar Shade
Loar Shade.description: As with all [[Shades_(Shades_of_Mort'ton)|shades in Mort'ton]], Loar shades possess 2 traits you should be aware of:

Portal frame.name: Portal frame
Portal frame.description: Failing to conjure the portal twice in a row will cause the portal frame to break, which prevents additional attempts at conjuring it (and accessing the coffin on the other side).

Gorilla Statue.name: Gorilla Statue
Gorilla Statue.description: The altar is very convenient while training on [[monkey guard]]s inside the temple.

Superior dragon bones.name: Superior dragon bones
Superior dragon bones.description: These bones can be used for the best Prayer experience in the game, but they are very expensive; when used at a [[gilded altar]], they require {{NoCoins|{{GEP|Superior dragon bones}}/525}} [[coins]] per experience, while regular [[dragon bones]] use {{NoCoins|{{GEP|Dragon bones}}/252}} coins per experience. As such, the most economical use is as a secondary for making [[super antifire potion]]s.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Bu.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Buy limits
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Bu.description: The '''buy limits''' of [[Grand Exchange]] items is restricted to a certain quantity every 4 hours. The following is the list of buying limits for all items in the Grand Exchange as of '''{{#time: j F Y|{{REVISIONTIMESTAMP}}}}'''.{{purge}}

Bank Deposit Pot.name: Bank Deposit Pot
Bank Deposit Pot.description: The '''Bank Deposit Pot''' is a [[bank deposit box]] located on [[Ape Atoll]], right next to a [[Bank chest]]. It can only be used after the completion of [[Monkey Madness II]].

Fiyr remains.name: Fiyr remains
Fiyr remains.description: To burn the fiyr remains, first place [[magic pyre logs|magic]] or [[redwood pyre logs]] on a [[Funeral Pyre|funeral pyre]], followed by the fiyr remains, then light the pyre with a [[tinderbox]]. This will grant the player [[Firemaking]] and [[Prayer]] experience (see table). Once burned, a silver or gold [[shade key]], or some [[coins]], will appear next to the pyre.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ob.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Obor Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ob.description: The '''Obor Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Obor]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Opal bolts (e).name: Opal bolts (e)
Opal bolts (e).description: Opal bolts are crafted by gem-tipping [[bronze bolts]] with [[opal bolt tips]].

Maximum magic hit.name: Maximum magic hit
Maximum magic hit.description: In most cases, the [[Tumeken's shadow]] provides the highest maximum magic hit possible. The exceptions to this are the [[Volatile nightmare staff|Volatile nightmare staff's]] [[Special attacks|special attack]], the [[Accursed sceptre|Accursed sceptre's]] special attack while in the [[wilderness]], the Accursed sceptre's against [[Revenants]] in the wilderness while wearing an [[Amulet of avarice]] and having [[Forinthry surge|Forinthry Surge]], and [[barrage spells]] when hitting up to nine targets.

The Forsaken Assassin.name: The Forsaken Assassin
The Forsaken Assassin.description: He will also throw bottles of poison on the player's current tile that are indicated by a throwing animation. He will throw three in a row, which can be avoided by moving away when the throwing animation begins. Otherwise, they will deal a high amount of damage and inflict poison. The Assassin will always perform an auto-attack almost immediately after throwing the third bottle.

Amulet of bounty.name: Amulet of bounty
Amulet of bounty.description: The amulet begins with 10 charges. When equipped, there is a 25% chance to use one [[seed]] instead of three when planting them in [[allotment]] patches, consuming 1 charge. After all charges are used, the amulet will crumble to dust.

Ferocious barbarian spirit.name: Ferocious barbarian spirit
Ferocious barbarian spirit.description: Making the pyre requires a [[tinderbox]] or any [[Barbarian Firemaking|suitable bow]] in your inventory, as well as mangled bones and any type of log and axe. After obtaining all required items, head to the edge of the lake in front of Otto the barbarian's hut and click on the "build pyre" spot.

Vorkath's head.name: Vorkath's head
Vorkath's head.description: It can be combined with a [[Slayer helmet]] or [[Slayer helmet (i)]] to create a [[turquoise slayer helmet|turquoise Slayer helmet]] or [[turquoise slayer helmet (i)|turquoise Slayer helmet (i)]], respectively. Doing so requires purchasing the ability ''Undead Head'' for 1,000 [[Slayer reward point]]s.

Pay-to-play Magic training.name: Pay-to-play Magic training
Pay-to-play Magic training.description: At higher levels, Magic can be trained much faster through casting multi-target [[burst spells|burst]] or [[barrage spells]] on [[Ancient Magicks]]. An efficient way to do this is on [[Slayer]] tasks, as certain [[Slayer monsters]] (such as [[dust devil]]s and [[Greater Nechryael]]) can be bursted or barraged for fast Slayer experience.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Hi.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/High Trade Volume Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Hi.description: The '''High Volume Trade Index''' is made up of a weighted average of the highest volume traded items listed in the [[Market Watch]], with the starting date of this average being 6 April 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of these high trade volume item prices are reflected in this index.

Fayrg bones.name: Fayrg bones
Fayrg bones.description: If burying the fayrg bones in [[Jiggig]], there's a 1 in 3{{fact}} chance to give no Prayer experience, and to instead spawn a [[skogre]]. The skogre will despawn after 5 minutes. A message in the chatbox appears "The creature rises from the grave... again!".

Spiritual ranger.name: Spiritual ranger
Spiritual ranger.description: As with all other [[spiritual creature]]s, their stats and combat capabilities vary.

Phantom Muspah.name: Phantom Muspah
Phantom Muspah.description: The Phantom Muspah is stronger than its quest variant, but otherwise shares the same attacks and mechanics. All forms of the Phantom Muspah have 33% freeze resistance, meaning it will only stay frozen for 66% of the base freeze duration of [[ice spells]].

Altar (Camdozaal).name: Altar (Camdozaal)
Altar (Camdozaal).description: According to [[Ramarno]] the altar was used by the [[Imcando dwarf|Imcando dwarves]] in offerings to [[Saradomin]]. The altar features a heavily damaged, but still recognisable [[Zaros]]ian symbol.

Damage per second/Magic.name: Damage per second/Magic
Damage per second/Magic.description: There are various methods by which players can increase their potential '''[[Magic]] damage'''. The effects of most equipped items can be seen in the [[Equipment Stats|stats window]] (labelled as Magic: +x and Magic damage: +x%).

Ghast.name: Ghast
Ghast.description: When deciding to attack a player, ghasts have a 7/10 chance of completely missing them. In the remaining 3/10 of cases, the ghast will perform a rot attack if food is present in the player's inventory, or deal 1-3 points of damage if not.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1534462628155752449|date=8 June 2022|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/SfF2z|archivedate=10 January 2023|quote=They have a 30% chance of doing the rot attack rather than "just missing you", though the higher tiers of Morytania legs would block it.}} Regardless of the outcome, the ghast will then retreat several game squares before re-targeting the player.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ru.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Rune Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ru.description: The '''Rune Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current runes listed in the [[Market Watch]], with the starting date of this average being 13 June 2020, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of rune prices is reflected in this index.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/To.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Tombs of Amascut Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/To.description: The '''Tombs of Amascut Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Tombs of Amascut]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 4 September 2022, at an index of 100.

Necklace of anguish.name: Necklace of anguish
Necklace of anguish.description: Players can attach an [[anguish ornament kit]], obtained from [[master clue scroll]]s, to create a [[necklace of anguish (or)]]. This is only cosmetic, and does not affect the necklace's stat bonuses. It can be dismantled, returning the necklace and ornament kit.

Ourania teleport (tablet).name: Ourania teleport (tablet)
Ourania teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Lunar)|lunar lectern]] in the ceremonial building on [[Lunar Isle]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 1 [[law rune]], 6 [[earth rune]]s, and 2 [[astral rune]]s, as well as level 71 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Lunar spellbook]].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ra.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Raw Food Index

Bones.name: Bones
Bones.description: Players may also use the [[Bones to Bananas]] or [[Bones to Peaches]] [[spells]] to turn normal bones to edible [[banana]]s or [[peach]]es.

Small zombie monkey bones.name: Small zombie monkey bones
Small zombie monkey bones.description: [[Zooknock]] is able to make a [[Zombie monkey greegree (small)|small zombie monkey greegree]] with the bones in the Ape Atoll Dungeon. If players want to make a [[Zombie monkey greegree (big)|big zombie monkey greegree]], they must use [[large zombie monkey bones]] instead. After completion of [[Monkey Madness II]], players no longer need to bring bones; they can simply claim the greegree from [[Zooknock]] in the [[Tree Gnome Stronghold]].

Malicious ashes.name: Malicious ashes
Malicious ashes.description: The [[ash sanctifier]] will automatically purify these [[Remains#Demonic ashes|demonic ashes]] for 32.5 experience if the [[Hard Kourend & Kebos Diary]] has been completed and 65 experience if the [[Elite Kourend & Kebos Diary]] is completed.

Ectofuntus.name: Ectofuntus
Ectofuntus.description: The Ectofuntus may be worshipped by clicking on it to consume a [[bucket of slime]] and any type of [[bonemeal]] held in your inventory. Bonemeal may be obtained by crushing any type of bones into a [[pot]] using the [[bone grinder]] found on the upper floor of the temple. Buckets of slime may be obtained by filling a [[bucket]] from the [[Pool of Slime]] found in the underground area below a nearby trapdoor. They may also be purchased from a [[Charter Crewmember]] on the [[Port Phasmatys]] dock.

Necklace of passage.name: Necklace of passage
Necklace of passage.description: Right-clicking the necklace in your inventory and selecting "rub", or right-clicking it while equipped will allow the player to teleport to one of three possible locations. Using the necklace to teleport will consume a charge. After all five charges are used, the necklace will disintegrate into dust.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ph.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Phantom Muspah Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ph.description: The '''Phantom Muspah Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Phantom Muspah]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 18 January 2023, at an index of 100.

Zamorak altar.name: Zamorak altar
Zamorak altar.description: The '''Zamorak altar''' is one of the five [[altar]]s found in the [[God Wars Dungeon]]. The altar can be used while fighting [[K'ril Tsutsaroth]], as long as the player is not currently in combat. It can also be used to teleport out of the room at any time.

Steel kiteshield (Saradomin).name: Steel kiteshield (Saradomin)
Steel kiteshield (Saradomin).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to create the kiteshield. Players can use an easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Ensouled monkey head.name: Ensouled monkey head
Ensouled monkey head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ca.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Callisto Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Ca.description: The '''Callisto Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Callisto]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

Calculator:Magic/Making tablets.name: Calculator:Magic/Making tablets
Calculator:Magic/Making tablets.description: Making magic tablets requires that the player has the appropriate [[Magic]] level.

Ensouled elf head.name: Ensouled elf head
Ensouled elf head.description: Ensouled heads can be reanimated anywhere as long as the head is on the ground within the 31x31 area centred on its initial drop location and has not been put into the [[bank]], [[trade]] screen, [[Grand Exchange]], or [[price checker]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1289279363532435461|date=31 July 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/OqtAp|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=About 15 tiles from where the object was dropped.}}{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1269309943422877696|date=6 June 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/7NPVB|archivedate=8 September 2021|quote=There are two versions of those heads. The version obtained from the dragon can be reanimated in the same area that it was dropped. It's untradeable. If you try to put it in the trade screen or GE, it transforms to a tradeable version that can only reanimate at the Dark Altar.}} Otherwise, it must be taken to the [[Dark Altar]] in [[Arceuus]] to be reanimated.

Zogre bones.name: Zogre bones
Zogre bones.description: If burying the zogre bones in [[Jiggig]], there's a 1 in 3{{fact}} chance to give no Prayer experience, and to instead spawn a [[skogre]]. The skogre will despawn after 5 minutes. A message in the chatbox appears "The creature rises from the grave... again!".

Rune heraldic helm (Saradomin).name: Rune heraldic helm (Saradomin)
Rune heraldic helm (Saradomin).description: Players need level 70 [[Prayer]] in order to create the helm. Players can use a stand or easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Ghost.name: Ghost
Ghost.description: Players must kill [[Ghost (Melzar's Maze)|ghosts]] in [[Melzar's Maze]] to progress through a level of the maze. The ghosts in Melzar's Maze can be spoken to with a [[Ghostspeak amulet]]; their speech hints that they were victims of [[Elvarg]] the dragon.

Reanimated dragon.name: Reanimated dragon
Reanimated dragon.description: Players are advised to bring some sort of [[dragonfire]] protection or make use of [[safespot]]s as the dragon is capable of using dragonfire.

Rune kiteshield (Saradomin).name: Rune kiteshield (Saradomin)
Rune kiteshield (Saradomin).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to create the kiteshield. Players can use an easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Abyssal ashes.name: Abyssal ashes
Abyssal ashes.description: The [[ash sanctifier]] will automatically purify these [[Remains#Demonic ashes|demonic ashes]] for 42.5 experience if the [[Hard Kourend & Kebos Diary]] has been completed, and 85 experience if the [[Elite Kourend & Kebos Diary]] is completed.

Cockatrice head.name: Cockatrice head
Cockatrice head.description: Before it can be [[Cockatrice head (mounted)|mounted]] in a [[Skill Hall]] within a [[player-owned house]], it must be stuffed by the [[Taxidermist]] in [[Canifis]], where she will charge 2,000 coins and return a [[stuffed cockatrice head]] to the player. They can then mount the head using 2 [[teak plank]]s. When players take it to the Taxidermist, she will tell the player ''"A cockatrice! Beautiful, isn't it? Look at the plumage!"''

Ranged.name: Ranged
Ranged.description: The [[combat triangle]] dictates that rangers are strong against mages but weak against melee fighters.

Waterbirth teleport (tablet).name: Waterbirth teleport (tablet)
Waterbirth teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Lunar)|lunar lectern]] in the ceremonial building on [[Lunar Isle]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 1 [[law rune]], 1 [[water rune]], and 2 [[astral rune]]s, as well as level 72 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Lunar spellbook]].

Bonemeal (bones).name: Bonemeal (bones)
Bonemeal (bones).description: Along with a [[bucket of slime]], players may place a pot of bonemeal into the Ectofuntus, granting 18 [[Prayer]] [[experience]]. Equipping the full set of [[Zealot's robes]] will provide a 5% chance (1.25% per piece) to save both the bonemeal and bucket of slime while worshipping the [[Ectofuntus]].

Grand Exchange.name: Grand Exchange
Grand Exchange.description: In the event that a member lists a sell offer and then their membership expires prior to fulfillment, the trade remains active and the item will sell when the price rises. No restriction exists on selling items, regardless of memberships status. However, if a player has been logged out for several days, any unfulfilled offers will pause until they log back in.

Bank Deposit Chest.name: Bank Deposit Chest
Bank Deposit Chest.description: One of them can be found in the underground portion of the [[Shilo Village mine]], which requires completion of the [[Karamja Diary#Medium|Medium Karamja Diary]] to access.

Armour/Prayer armour.name: Armour/Prayer armour
Armour/Prayer armour.description: '''Prayer armour''' is used to slow the rate at which [[Prayer points]] drain when [[praying]]. Unlike the other three general categories of [[armour]], there are few items within it that can be considered uniquely Prayer-related. Many [[shield]]s, magic [[robes]], and types of [[metal]] armour can also be considered Prayer armour.

Necklace of faith.name: Necklace of faith
Necklace of faith.description: When worn, the necklace will restore the wearer's [[prayer point]]s by 25% of [[Prayer]] level if their [[hitpoint]]s drop below 20% of their maximum. Once the effect takes place, the necklace will degrade to dust. However, if the player is reduced to zero hitpoints from above 20%, the necklace will have no effect and the player will die as usual.

Hydra bones.name: Hydra bones
Hydra bones.description: Burying them while wearing a [[dragonbone necklace]] will restore 4 prayer points.

Torag the Corrupted.name: Torag the Corrupted
Torag the Corrupted.description: Torag is often regarded as the easiest brother since his set effect does not pose a notable threat in combat and he is inaccurate compared to the rest of the brothers. He attacks using hammers, so armour defensive against crush is advised. Despite his inaccuracy, he can still hit up to 24 so the use of [[Protect from Melee]] is advised for players with low [[Defence]]. Protect from Melee does '''not''' prevent his effect from activating.

Combat Options.name: Combat Options
Combat Options.description: There currently isn't a player wieldable melee weapon that calculates accuracy from magic or ranged bonus, but there is ranged weapon, the [[dwarf multicannon]], which calculates accuracy using the player's Ranged or melee bonus depending on the weapon and attack style, detailed in [[Dwarf_multicannon#Accuracy|the accuracy section]] of its page.

Special attacks.name: Special attacks
Special attacks.description: Special attacks offer a variety of benefits, including temporary boosts in [[stats]], restoration of [[health]] or [[prayer]], and extra damage or accuracy. If a weapon has a special attack, hovering over the special attack bar, or '''spec bar''', will show the player a tooltip with a weapon's unique special attack name and description.

Ironman Guide/Prayer.name: Ironman Guide/Prayer
Ironman Guide/Prayer.description: [[Prayer]] is a slower skill to train for ironmen due to having to obtain bones themselves. Ideally, it is best to use every bone on an [[experience]] boosting altar, such as the [[Chaos Temple (hut)|Chaos Altar]], [[Ectofuntus]], [[Libation bowl]], or with high [[Construction]], a [[gilded altar]] in the [[chapel]] of your [[player-owned house]]. A [[bone crusher]] or [[ash sanctifier]] can be used for passive experience while training when the bones dropped are not worth picking up.

Life leech.name: Life leech
Life leech.description: Sources of life leech often share a similar graphical style, a visible upwards flourish above the target when triggered in combat. This makes them easy to spot compared to attacks that do not trigger the effect.

Mycelium pool.name: Mycelium pool
Mycelium pool.description: The pool holds up to 28 fossils, 10 [[calcite]], and 10 [[pyrophosphite]]. The fossils can be either unidentified or cleaned. However, [[plant fossils]] cannot be enriched and will be '''instantly destroyed''' if added to the pool. [[Unidentified large fossil]]s have a chance to be plant fossils, so cleaning those fossils is '''not''' recommended if planning to use them at the mycelium pool.

Adamant kiteshield (Saradomin).name: Adamant kiteshield (Saradomin)
Adamant kiteshield (Saradomin).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to make the kiteshield. Players can use an easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/The Whisperer Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Th.description: The '''The Whisperer Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[The Whisperer]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 11 October 2024, at an index of 100.

Karil the Tainted.name: Karil the Tainted
Karil the Tainted.description: His set effect does not pose a threat in combat however his attacks are very accurate even on players with high defensive bonuses, so players may find it difficult navigating to the chest later with a lower Agility level (and as a result, less [[energy]]). As such, it is strongly recommended to activate [[Protect from Missiles]] - note that this does not prevent his set effect from activating. The use of a [[super restore]] potion may be worth using after the fight if the player's Agility stat has been drained significantly.

Adamant heraldic helm (Saradomin).name: Adamant heraldic helm (Saradomin)
Adamant heraldic helm (Saradomin).description: Players need level 70 [[Prayer]] in order to create the helm. Players can use a stand or easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Fiyr Shade.name: Fiyr Shade
Fiyr Shade.description: As with all [[Shades (Shades of Mort'ton)|shades in Mort'ton]], Fiyr shades possess 2 traits you should be aware of:

Pasty jogre bones.name: Pasty jogre bones
Pasty jogre bones.description: '''{{Colour|Red|Warning}}:''' Pasty jogre bones made from [[Karambwanji paste (cooked)|cooked karambwanji paste]] will explode, dealing 2 damage, when cooked. Players will receive the message: ''"The cooked karambwanji paste catches fire and explodes."''

Amulet of fury.name: Amulet of fury
Amulet of fury.description: While it is generally regarded as the most versatile amulet with the best all-around bonuses, several amulets [[Amulet of fury#Comparison with other amulets|surpass it in certain areas]].

Emerald bolts (e).name: Emerald bolts (e)
Emerald bolts (e).description: These are commonly used by low-level [[Player killing|PKers]] to inflict poison. They are also common when fighting the [[Corporeal Beast]], to [[Stun (status)|stun]] the [[Dark energy core]].

Khazard teleport (tablet).name: Khazard teleport (tablet)
Khazard teleport (tablet).description: Players can create this item on the [[Lectern (Lunar)|lunar lectern]] in the ceremonial building on [[Lunar Isle]] with a piece of [[soft clay]], 2 [[law rune]]s, 4 [[water rune]]s, and 2 [[astral rune]]s, as well as level 78 [[Magic]] while being on the [[Lunar spellbook]].

Rune kiteshield (Zamorak).name: Rune kiteshield (Zamorak)
Rune kiteshield (Zamorak).description: Players must have 70 [[Prayer]] or more in order to create the kiteshield. Players can use an easel in another player's house if they do not have one in theirs.

Iron bar.name: Iron bar
Iron bar.description: An iron bar can be smithed on an [[anvil]] through the Smithing skill to create [[iron weapons]] and [[Iron armour|armour]]. When smithed, each bar grants 25 experience, with a maximum of 125 being given for the [[iron platebody]].

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Cr.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Crazy archaeologist Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Cr.description: The '''Crazy archaeologist Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Crazy archaeologist]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 23 June 2021, at an index of 100. The overall rising and falling of food prices is reflected in this index.

Autocast.name: Autocast
Autocast.description: Selecting the option without the shield will cast magic offensively, granting Magic experience. Selecting the "shield" option will cast magic defensively, dividing the experience gained between the [[Defence]] and Magic skills.

Basilisk head.name: Basilisk head
Basilisk head.description: Before it can be [[Basilisk head (mounted)|mounted]] in a [[Skill Hall]] within a [[player-owned house]], it must be stuffed by the [[Taxidermist]] in [[Canifis]], where she will charge 4,000 coins and return a [[stuffed basilisk head]] to the player. They can then mount the head using 2 [[teak plank]]s. When players take it to the Taxidermist, she will tell the player ''"My, he's a scary-looking fellow, isn't it? He'll look good on your wall!"''

Ring of suffering.name: Ring of suffering
Ring of suffering.description: Players can make one by enchanting a [[zenyte ring]] with the [[Lvl-7 Enchant]] spell. This requires level 93 [[Magic]], 20 [[soul rune]]s, 20 [[blood rune]]s, and 1 [[cosmic rune]] and grants 110 Magic experience. As with all enchanted [[zenyte]] jewellery, this ring requires a [[Hitpoints]] level of 75 in order to be equipped.

Statue (Darkmeyer).name: Statue (Darkmeyer)
Statue (Darkmeyer).description: The statue is also part of the [[Darkmeyer Display]] found at the lower level of the [[Old School Museum]] underneath the [[Falador Party Room]]. Praying at this statue does not damage the player.

Treus Dayth.name: Treus Dayth
Treus Dayth.description: Treus Dayth can be fought in the [[Nightmare Zone]] after completion of the [[Haunted Mine]] quest; however, he will not have any obstacles to command and can only use his melee attack, and is therefore very easy to kill, especially with [[Ranged]]. Killing Treus Dayth will not award Slayer experience in Nightmare Zone.

RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Co.name: RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Commander Zilyana Index
RuneScape:Grand Exchange Market Watch/Co.description: The '''Commander Zilyana Index''' is made up of a weighted average of all of the current unique and non-unique drops listed in the [[Commander Zilyana]] drop table, with the starting date of this average being 3 July 2021, at an index of 100.

User:Nicolb2305/Sandbox2.name: User:Nicolb2305/Sandbox2
User:Nicolb2305/Sandbox2.description: A '''bank chest''' is an interactive scenery item that allows quick access to a player's [[bank]] account, usually found in remote locations or places where a normal bank would not fit. Like any other banking facility it is indicated with a bank icon ([[File:Bank icon.png|($)]]).

Ensouled imp head.name: Ensouled imp head
Ensouled imp head.description: It can be reanimated using the level 16 [[Magic]] spell [[Basic Reanimation]] from the [[Arceuus spellbook]], granting 32 Magic experience. Killing a [[reanimated imp]] gives 286 Prayer experience.
